|BOSSID|96759| |LVL|110| |NAME|Helya| |MAPID|1042| |ST|This encounter is a complicated three-phase fight with extremely high movement and awareness requirements. Players will first fight off the tentacles (npc:96759) is using to Siege the Naglfar, while (npc:96759) slings spells at the party. Once players have defeated 6 tentacles, (npc:96759) will Submerge briefly, then rise up from beneath the boat to Breach the bow and engage the players directly.<br/><br/>Players must always be aware of what is happening in the space around them, and must frequently check (npc:96759)'s facing to avoid deadly mechanics.<br/><br/>Siege Phase (100%-80%):During the Siege phase, players do not fight (npc:96759) directly, but must kill the (npc:99801)s and (npc:100360)s that periodically spawn.<br/><br/>(npc:100360)s spawn on the edge of the boat and have no abilities. (npc:99801)s burst up through the deck and must be tanked.<br/><br/>Players should prioritize the (npc:99801)s over the (npc:100360)s, but should multi-DoT when possible.<br/><br/>Additionally, players must avoid the (npc:100188)s that burst up through the deck of the boat periodically.<br/><br/>Throughout the Siege phase, (npc:96759) will also assault the party with two spells: (spell:197805), which deals light, random damage to 2 players every 3-5 seconds, and cannot be avoided; and (spell:197264).<br/><br/>Submerge Phase:Once 6 tentacles have died and (npc:96759) has reached 80% health, she will Submerge. During this phase, there is nothing for players to attack; they must simply survive.<br/><br/>This Submerge phase lasts for 20 seconds, and will reoccur again periodically during the final phase of the fight (approximately every 90 seconds).<br/><br/>Breach Phase:At the end of the Submerge phase, (npc:96759) will rise up from the ocean and break off the bow of the ship so she can reach the players.<br/><br/>In addition, (npc:96759) gains the (spell:227233) ability.<br/><br/>(npc:96759) will concede and slink away when she reaches 70% health remaining. A chest will spawn on the deck for players to loot.<br/><br/>Because the first phase's tentacles are not necessarily always active, it is best to save (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) for when (npc:96759) emerges and begins phase 3.| |DPS|<b>During the first phase, prioritize (npc:99801)s over (npc:100360)s, but multi-DoT and cleave when possible<br/><b>During and after the Submerged phase, avoid the (spell:197858) and move away from (npc:100188)s<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:197805) when possible<br/><b>Avoid (spell:227233) by watching for (npc:96759)'s facing and moving to a safe space| |HEAL|<b>Dispel (spell:197264) immediately, unless the party is on extremely low health<br/><b>Use raid CDs if multiple players are struck by (spell:227233), or if players are low after a (spell:197264) dispel<br/><b>Tank damage will be steady, and party damage is spiky, so be prepared to cast quick single-target heals<br/><b>During and after the Submerged phase, avoid the (spell:197858) and move away from (npc:100188)s<br/><b>Avoid (spell:227233) by watching for (npc:96759)'s facing and moving to a safe space| |TANK|<b>During the first phase, quickly move to and pick up the (npc:99801) spawns<br/><b>During and after the Submerged phase, avoid the (spell:197858) and move away from (npc:100188)s<br/><b>While fighting (npc:96759), point her towards one side of the boat so melee DPS can attack from the other side<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:197805) when possible<br/><b>Avoid (spell:227233) by watching for (npc:96759)'s facing and moving to a safe space<br/><b>Stay in melee range so Wing Buffet is never triggered| 
|BOSSID|98205| |LVL|110| |NAME|Corstilax| |MAPID|1079| |ST|This encounter is a single-target fight with moderate movement requirements. Players can occasionally gain strong Haste buffs and may wish to align short-duration throughput cooldowns with them.<br/><br/>Shortly into the fight, (npc:98205) will target a non-tank player with (spell:196068).<br/><br/>(npc:98205) will occasionally place a DPS player in (spell:195791).<br/><br/>Frequently, (npc:98205) will summon a (spell:220481) near a ranged player. The (spell:220481) persists for a minute and deals heavy damage to all nearby players each second. Players should move away from these orbs and avoid running near them while handling (spell:196068) or other mechanics.<br/><br/>About 15 seconds into the fight, and again at 30- or 60-second intervals thereafter, an (spell:195523) will spill (spell:195362) into the encounter area.<br/><br/>30 seconds into the fight, and every 50 seconds thereafter, (npc:98205) will cast (spell:196115).<br/><br/>Note that once (spell:196115) ends, players retain any (spell:195362) stacks they may still have. This can occur if the player gained more than 8 (spell:195362) stacks, or if the player used a movement ability to outrange the (spell:196115) before all their stacks were removed.<br/><br/>Two sets of (spell:195362) pools will spawn between the first and second (spell:196115) casts, so players can accumulate a very high number of (spell:195362) stacks during this time. Take care only to do so if you have enough mobility options to avoid the (spell:203649) stun. In a long fight, e.g. on high Mythic+ levels, players who take advantage of this can maintain very high (spell:195362) stacks for the rest of the encounter.| |DPS|<b>If targeted by (spell:196068), run away to drop the missiles away from other players and avoid being struck by them<br/><b>Free nearby players from (spell:195791) by clicking on the floating prison<br/><b>Gain up to, but no more than, 8 stacks of (spell:195362)<br/><b><br/><b>Run away from (npc:98205) during (spell:196115), or use a movement speed ability towards the end, to avoid (spell:203649) damage<br/><b>Move away from nearby (spell:220481)s| |HEAL|<b>Moderate party healing is necessary during (spell:196068)<br/><b>Quickly switch to the (spell:195791) target and focus single-target healing on them until freed<br/><b>Dispel the (spell:203649) stun from any affected players<br/><b>Save throughput cooldowns for any (spell:196115)/(spell:203649) that deals damage to multiple party members<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:196068), run away to drop the missiles away from other players and avoid being struck by them<br/><b>Free nearby players from (spell:195791) by clicking on the floating prison<br/><b>Run away from (npc:98205) during (spell:196115), or use a movement speed ability towards the end, to avoid (spell:203649) damage<br/><b>Move away from nearby (spell:220481)s| |TANK|<b>Run away from (npc:98205) before (spell:196115) ends, or use a strong damage-reduction cooldown to reduce its damage<br/><b>Never gain more than 8 stacks of (spell:195362), to avoid the (spell:203649) stun at the end of (spell:196115)| 
