|BOSSID|98207| |LVL|110| |NAME|Nal'tira| |MAPID|1079| |ST|Once players have cleared the last wave of (npc:98759)s from (npc:98207)'s Lair, (npc:98207) will drop down from the ceiling. Players should stay out of the middle of the room to avoid pulling her before the party is ready.<br/><br/>The (npc:98207) encounter is straightforward, with moderate movement requirements. About 30 seconds into the fight, and every 20 seconds thereafter, (npc:98207) will summon a (npc:98759) add that players must quickly kill. The fight is otherwise a single-target encounter.<br/><br/>The (npc:98759)s that spawn during the (npc:98207) fight are identical to the trash mobs of the same name.<br/><br/>(npc:98207) will periodically use (spell:199811), teleporting to a player at range.<br/><br/>After (spell:199811), (npc:98207) will cast (spell:200040), firing off two bolts of toxic poison.<br/><br/>Pools of (spell:200040) last for 5 minutes, so the room will slowly fill up, reducing the available space players have to counter other mechanics. Ranged players should try to stand near an existing (spell:200040) pool so that the next (spell:200040) cast will overlap and take up less space.<br/><br/>Shortly after casting (spell:200040), (npc:98207) will link two DPS players together with (spell:200227).<br/><br/>If the party wishes to use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) on (npc:98207), the start of the encounter is the best time, as there is less movement required and less obstruction from (spell:200040).| |DPS|<b>Prioritize killing the (npc:98759) when it spawns<br/><b>Ranged DPS should stay at maximum range, so that (spell:200227) falls off quickly when ranged and melee DPS are linked<br/><b>When targeted by (spell:200227), run away from the other target, and use a movement ability or a defensive cooldown to reduce damage<br/><b>When (npc:98207) uses (spell:199811), quickly move away from her front to avoid the damage<br/><b>Move out of the (spell:200040) pools to avoid the severe Haste reduction| |HEAL|<b>Players affected by (spell:200227) will need focused healing<br/><b>The tank will take additional damage while the (npc:98759) is alive<br/><b>Melee DPS may often take heavy damage from (spell:199811)<br/><b>Use cooldowns to recover from (spell:199811) and (spell:200227) mistakes<br/><b>When (npc:98207) uses (spell:199811), quickly move away from her front to avoid the damage<br/><b>Move out of the (spell:200040) pools to avoid the severe Haste reduction| |TANK|<b>Quickly taunt the (npc:98759) add when it spawns<br/><b>Use a cooldown if the (npc:98759) targets you with (spell:211543)<br/><b>When (npc:98207) blinks back for the second half of (spell:199811), move to her side to avoid the damage<br/><b>Move (npc:98207) away from nearby pools of (spell:200040)| 
|BOSSID|98208| |LVL|110| |NAME|Advisor Vandros| |MAPID|1079| |ST|(npc:98208) is a two-phase fight with very heavy movement requirements and high situational awareness is required. The second phase, (spell:203935), occurs when (npc:98208) reaches 50% health, and will teleport players away from the boss to another location in the dungeon. Players should plan their DPS throughput cooldowns around this forced-downtime window, and many groups prefer to use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) upon returning from this phase.<br/><br/>When players initially encounter (npc:98208), he will be channeling a protective bubble in a large area around him. This will fade as soon as players interact with the boss.<br/><br/>The first phase of the (npc:98208) is hectic and requires frequent movement. (npc:98208) will periodically summon 3 (npc:102849)s near players' locations.<br/><br/>About every 7 seconds, (npc:98208) will cast (spell:203176).<br/><br/>This may be best accomplished by letting (npc:98208) reach 2 stacks, then interrupting the next two casts; this should allow two players to handle the mechanic adequately. <br/><br/>Offensive dispel abilities such as (spell:370) and (spell:528) can also remove the buff, but these only remove a single stack at a time and are generally a less efficient method of countering this mechanic.<br/><br/>Approximately every 30 seconds, (npc:98208) will summon a pair of (spell:202974)s that function similarly to (npc:77428)'s (spell:157349) (from the Highmaul raid).<br/><br/>When (npc:98208) reaches 50% health, he will stop time and cast (spell:203882). The party will be teleported to one of the other bosses' rooms at random and must find their way back to (npc:98208)'s location within two minutes. If players do not re-engage (npc:98208) before the (spell:203882) debuff expires, the entire party will instantly die.<br/><br/>While banished, (npc:102849)s spawn at an accelerated rate, which results in heavy party damage unless meticulously avoided. The party must also defeat several (npc:103130)s along the path back to the boss.<br/><br/>It is important to keep moving during the (spell:203882) phase, and to stick with your party even if they are going the wrong way! It is usually recoverable if players start out in the wrong direction, as long as they stick together. If players split up, the lone player is very likely to die.<br/><br/>Players should use personal defensive cooldowns to help healers, since not all of them have the capacity to deal heavy AoE healing on the move.<br/><br/>Any (npc:103130) that players are in combat with when (npc:98208) is re-engaged will join the fight, and this will very likely be lethal. Defeat all (npc:103130)s in the path before engaging (npc:98208).<br/><br/>Once players re-engage (npc:98208), he will resume his Phase 1 abilities, but also gains a new ability, (spell:220871), which he will use every 40 seconds.<br/><br/>Due to the complexity added by (spell:220871), this phase is very dangerous, and players may wish to save strong DPS cooldowns to defeat (npc:98208) before a second (spell:220871) cast can occur.| |DPS|<b>Move away from nearby (npc:102849)s before they detonate<br/><b>Assist in the (spell:203176) interrupt rotation<br/><b>Use personal damage-reduction cooldowns and movement speed boosts during (spell:202974)<br/><b>During (spell:203882), quickly kill the (npc:103130)s and interrupt (spell:203957)<br/><b>Use major personal damage-reduction cooldowns while running back to (npc:98208), and avoid as much (npc:102849) damage as possible<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:220871), move away from other players, and keep moving until the debuff falls off| |HEAL|<b>Be sure to maintain line-of-sight on the tank at all times<br/><b>Heavy tank healing will be necessary when (npc:98208) has multiple stacks of (spell:203176)<br/><b>Throughput cooldowns are useful during (spell:202974)<br/><b>Move away from nearby (npc:102849)s before they detonate, and move quickly through (spell:202974)<br/><b>During (spell:203882), use instant-cast or mobile heals, and damage-reduction cooldowns (raid or personal), to mitigate heavy party damage<br/><b>Dispel (spell:203957) from affected players<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:220871), move away from other players, and keep moving until the debuff falls off| |TANK|<b>Move (npc:98208) away from nearby (npc:102849)s to avoid excessive damage<br/><b>Assist in the (spell:203176) interrupt rotation<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation and cooldowns when (npc:98208) has several stacks of (spell:203176)<br/><b>During (spell:203882), interrupt (npc:103130)s' (spell:203957) and focus on dealing damage to the (npc:103130)<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:220871), move in a straight line so melee DPS can still find places to stand and attack the boss without taking damage| 
