mely high damage<br/><b>The party should note when the two glaives are close together, and use that opportunity to run around them<br/><b>This may be necessary more than once, as the glaives will continue to trace a path through the room until (npc:95885) is dead<br/><b>Use a personal defensive cooldown or immunity to run through the (spell:214625) if you get trapped with no safe escape<br/><br/>Most parties use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) at the start of the encounter when little movement is necessary.| |DPS|<b>Interrupt (spell:191823) when possible<br/><b>Move out of impending (spell:202913) strikes before they hit, and move away from (spell:202919) patches<br/><b>If (npc:95885) assumes Vengeance form, watch for approaching (spell:197333)/(spell:214625) and go around the (spell:197333) to avoid taking (spell:214625) damage| |HEAL|<b>Tank damage is extremely heavy while (npc:95885) is buffed with (spell:191941)<br/><b>Use powerful single-target healing abilities or cooldowns to help the tank survive<br/><b>Move out of impending (spell:202913) strikes before they hit, and move away from (spell:202919) patches<br/><b>Party damage can range from light to moderate depending on which form (npc:95885) takes on after (spell:202740)<br/><b>Use raid cooldowns to heal the party during the second phase, so you can focus on tank healing and dodging mechanics<br/><b>If (npc:95885) assumes Vengeance form, watch for approaching (spell:197333)/(spell:214625) and go around the (spell:197333) to avoid taking (spell:214625) damage<br/><b>If (npc:95885) assumes Vengeance form, players who take (spell:214625)s damage may require emergency heals<br/><b>If you have to choose between the tank and a player taking (spell:214625)s, prioritize healing the tank| |TANK|<b>When possible, apply Active Mitigation for the entire 10-second duration of the (spell:191941) buff<br/><b>If Active Mitigation is not available, consider using a cooldown to mitigate (spell:191941) damage, as it can be very dangerous<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:191823) when possible<br/><b>Move (npc:95885) away from nearby patches of (spell:202919)<br/><b>If (npc:95885) assumes Havoc form, keep him faced away from the party so players do not take (spell:190836) damage<br/><b>Side-step out of the (spell:190836) beam to avoid taking heavy damage from it<br/><b>If (npc:95885) assumes Vengeance form, kite (npc:95885) around the room when (spell:197333)s approach the party, to avoid taking (spell:214625) damage| 
|BOSSID|96015| |LVL|110| |NAME|Inquisitor Tormentorum| |MAPID|1045| |ST|This encounter is complex due to the four different sets of adds the boss may call upon during the fight. Players will have to adjust to a shifting kill priority and be careful with avoiding the new mechanics these add packs bring.<br/><br/>(npc:96015) uses only one ability during the encounter: (spell:200905).<br/><br/>(npc:96015) will cast (spell:200905) about every 20 seconds. Whenever players notice the purple (spell:200905) beams coming from (npc:96015) to their characters, even if there are high-priority kill targets alive, players should quickly target (npc:96015) and attempt to interrupt the spell.<br/><br/>At 70% health, and again at 40% health, (npc:96015) will (spell:200898) to one of four prison cells and release its prisoners. Players should focus on defeating the prisoners quickly and handling their additional mechanics; the boss is not vulnerable to damage while he is unlocking the prisons.<br/><br/>Moving clockwise from (npc:96015)'s starting place, the four prison cells contain the following types of enemies:<br/><br/>Northwest cell block<br/>This cell block contains one (npc:99675) and two (npc:99676)s, enemies previously encountered in the Mogu'shan Vaults raid.<br/><br/>Players should prioritize killing the (npc:99676)s first, then the (npc:99675).<br/><br/>Northeast cell block<br/>This cell block contains a (npc:99655), a (npc:99657), and a (npc:99651).<br/><br/>Both the (npc:99657) and (npc:99651) adds will cast (spell:26043), increasing nearby enemies' attack power for 30 seconds. This can affect the boss and may persist after the prisoners are dead.<br/><br/>Prioritize killing the (npc:99657), then the (npc:99651), then the (npc:99655).<br/><br/>Southeast cell block<br/>This cell block contains 5 (npc:99678) adds, who only use melee attacks while alive. These enemies were previously encountered in the Siege of Orgrimmar raid.<br/><br/>Southwest cell block<br/>This cell bl