|BOSSID|114261| |LVL|110| |NAME|Toe Knee| |MAPID|1115| |ST|The Westfall Story encounter has three phases, and requires heavy movement. Save (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) for phase 3, which is the most hectic and dangerous.<br/><br/>Phase 1: The Defias Brotherhood<br/><br/>During this phase, players fight (npc:114261) and his three (npc:114265)s. The phase lasts until (npc:114261) is brought to 50% health.<br/><br/>(npc:114261) will use a combo of two fire-based abilities against the party, starting with (spell:227568).<br/><br/>Immediately after (spell:227568), (npc:114261) will lash out with (spell:227453).<br/><br/>To manage these two abilities, position the ranged DPS/healer in the corner of the stage, and tank (npc:114261) about 15-20 yards away. When he casts (spell:227568), the melee DPS and tanks should run out to the ranged and stand near them. (npc:114261) will then use (spell:227453) and place all the (spell:227480)s clumped together. The party then moves away in one direction, and the tank resets (npc:114261) to a safe distance from the ranged.<br/><br/>The (npc:114265)s use a single ability, (spell:227325), which they will cast every 10 seconds.<br/><br/>The strategy listed above should keep all of the (npc:114265)s close together most of the time so they can be AoEd.<br/><br/>When a (npc:114265)'s health is reduced to 0, they retire to the side of the stage and begin to dance. They will no longer use (spell:227325). The party should kill (npc:114265)s first, quickly, to reduce the damage of this phase.<br/><br/>Phase 2: The Fins<br/><br/>When (npc:114261) reaches 50% health, he will retire to the side of the stage with his dancing (npc:114265)s, and will begin to dance as well. (npc:114260) and her three (npc:114266) adds will then advance from the other side of the stage.<br/><br/>(npc:114260) uses powerful water- and storm-based abilities against the party.<br/><br/>About every 23 seconds, (npc:114260) will cast (spell:227783), summoning powerful waves that sweep across the stage.<br/><br/>Players will often have to deal with both (spell:227783) and (spell:227777) at the same time. This can lead to fatal damage if a player is struck by a wave just as their (spell:227777) is expiring.<br/><br/>In addition, the three (npc:114266) adds will frequently cast (spell:227420).<br/><br/>(spell:227420) can be interrupted and the (npc:114266)s are susceptible to AoE CC and stuns. As with the (npc:114265)s in phase 1, reducing the (npc:114266)s' health to zero will cause them to retreat to the side of the stage and dance, removing (spell:227420) from the encounter.<br/><br/>Players should focus on killing the (npc:114266)s first, and expect to spend a long time in this phase as the heavy movement requirements of (spell:227777) and (spell:227783) will limit DPS uptime on (npc:114260).<br/><br/>Phase 3: Somewhere<br/><br/>Once (npc:114260) is brought to 50% health, (npc:114261) will re-join the battle, and players must deal with both (npc:114260) and (npc:114261)'s abilities<br/><br/>The encounter area will quickly fill up with (spell:227480)s that can restrict the party's ability to react to (spell:227777) or (spell:227783). Continue to use the positioning from phase 2, since (spell:227783) and (spell:227777) are more potent, and more likely to be fatal. Tanks and melee must be sure to run out for (spell:227568), as a stun during (spell:227777) or (spell:227783) may cause a wipe.<br/><br/>Use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) for this phase to shorten it.<br/><br/>Both (npc:114261) and (npc:114260) must die for the encounter to end. The two bosses' health pools are not linked. Players should focus on killing one of the two bosses first to remove their abilities from the encounter; (npc:114260) is the most dangerous and should be the primary target.<br/><br/>(npc:114260) will become stunned when reduced to 0 health, while (npc:114261) will actually die - as in West Side Story - and it is his body that drops 