|BOSSID|114312| |LVL|110| |NAME|Moroes| |MAPID|1115| |ST|This encounter is an adds fight, but the best strategy for most groups will be to fight one enemy at a time, and to kill each of the adds before beginning to deal significant damage to (npc:114312).<br/><br/>(npc:114312) will have 4 dinner guests accompanying him in the banquet hall, chosen from a set of 6 possible NPCs. Each week, the set of dinner guests will be chosen randomly, but all players who attempt the Return to Karazhan dungeon that week will encounter the same dinner party.<br/><br/><b>(npc:114319) buffs (npc:114312) with (spell:227616), granting him 100% increased damage and 75% increased attack speed for 30 seconds<br/><b>(npc:114320) throws his (spell:227463) weapon at a random player, dealing moderate to heavy damage to players who remain near the blade<br/><b>(npc:114318) casts (spell:227646), dealing heavy damage to nearby players<br/><b>(npc:114321) uses (spell:227672), dealing heavy damage to all players in front of him, with a very obvious telegraph<br/><b>(npc:114316) will chain-cast (spell:227575) at random players, and will target one player with (spell:227545), which should be interrupted<br/><b>(npc:114317) chain-casts (spell:227542) at random targets, and will heal (npc:114312) with (spell:227578) if his health drops low enough<br/><br/>All of (npc:114312)' dinner guests are susceptible to the (spell:227908) item, which will stun the targeted undead for 1.2 minutes. The party should obtain at least 4 (spell:227908) from the Banquet Hall and adjacent rooms before engaging (npc:114312).<br/><br/>It is important to kill these adds before focusing on (npc:114312), because when (npc:114312) reaches 60% health, he will cast (spell:227872), making all his dinner guests immune to CC effects. Facing multiple dinner guests plus (npc:114312) will be too dangerous, and may lead to wipes, so it is safest to kill the adds first.<br/><br/>Before beginning the encounter, discuss which of the adds to leave active and kill first, and assign players to trap each of the other adds.<br/><br/>Once the first add is dead, the tank should use a ranged ability when possible to pull the next add to be killed. Continue in this careful fashion until all four adds are dead.<br/><br/>(npc:114312) himself has fairly straightforward mechanics, and will be active the entire time the party is fighting the adds. <br/><br/>(npc:114312) will use (spell:227742) on random players.<br/><br/>(npc:114312) will also attack the tank with (spell:227832), which reduces the tank's armor by 75%. This can be very dangerous, especially while fighting adds, but (spell:227832) can be dispelled by all healers.<br/><br/>The aim is to kill (npc:114312) before the healing becomes unmanageable due to multiple (spell:227742) stacks on each player. If the adds are dealt with properly, the party can save (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) to burn down (npc:114312) once the four adds are dead.| |DPS|<b>At the start of the encounter, target your assigned add and use your (spell:227908) extra action button to trap it<br/><b>Be very careful not to spread DoTs or AoE damage to the trapped adds while attacking (npc:114312) or the designated add<br/><b>Focus DPS on the add, and be sure not to drop (npc:114312) below 60% before the adds are dead<br/><b>When each add is active:<br/><b>Interrupt (npc:114319)'s (spell:227616)<br/><b>Interrupt (npc:114317)'s (spell:227542)<br/><b>Avoid (npc:114321)'s (spell:227672) by stepping out of the telegraphed area<br/><b>Move away from (npc:114318) during (spell:227646)<br/><b>Move out of (npc:114320)'s (spell:227463)<br/><b>Interrupt (npc:114316)'s (spell:227545) ability<br/><b>Use DPS cooldowns against (npc:114312) when the adds are dead<br/><b>If you have multiple stacks of (spell:227742), use personal defensive CDs as frequently as possible| |HEAL|<b>At the start of the encounter, target your assigned add and use your (spell:227908) extra action button to trap it<br