|BOSSID|114262| |LVL|110| |NAME|Attumen the Huntsman| |MAPID|1115| |ST|This encounter has two phases: a mounted phase, where (npc:114262) rides his steed, (npc:114264); and a dismounted phase, which occurs when (npc:114264) reaches 50% health. During the dismounted phase, (npc:114264) will slowly regain her health, and when she reaches full health, (npc:114262) will leap onto her back, resetting the fight to the first phase.<br/><br/>This is a single-target fight, as (npc:114262) is not attackable during Phase 1 and (npc:114264) is not attackable during Phase 2. The encounter requires moderate movement and good awareness.<br/><br/>Note that only the damage on (npc:114262) really matters; (npc:114264) heals back to full each time the party pushes the fight to Phase 2. Players should save their most powerful cooldowns for the (npc:114262) phases.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Horse and Rider as One<br/><br/>The encounter begins with (npc:114262) riding atop (npc:114264). Players will attack (npc:114264), but both (npc:114264) and (npc:114262) will attack players.<br/><br/>Every 30 seconds during this phase, (npc:114262) will cast (spell:227404) on the party.<br/><br/>(npc:114264) will also use the (spell:227363) ability, dealing heavy Fire damage to all players within 30 yards, and interrupting any spells being cast. Ranged DPS and healers should stand at max range to avoid these effects.<br/><br/>(npc:114262) will attack the tank with (spell:227636), and commands (npc:114264) to attack the tank with (spell:227638), both of which deal frequent tank damage.<br/><br/>When (npc:114264) reaches 50% health, (npc:114262) will leap down from the saddle and interact directly with the party.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Fighting on Foot<br/><br/>During this phase, players attack (npc:114262) directly. Unlike (npc:114264), (npc:114262)'s health will not replenish during his 'off' phase, and the encounter can only end if players kill (npc:114262). The party should use its major DPS cooldowns here to burst (npc:114262) down and end the fight in as few Phase 2 repeats as possible.<br/><br/>Although (npc:114264) is not attackable, she will continue to attack the party with (spell:227339), a cone-shaped charge attack.<br/><br/>While dismounted, (npc:114262) will attack the tank with (spell:227493), typically twice per phase.<br/><br/>Shortly after the first (spell:227493) cast, (npc:114262) will attack with (spell:228852), another cone attack.<br/><br/>The recommended strategy for dealing with these three mechanics is to mark a position in the room where the party will stack for (spell:228852).<br/><br/>While (npc:114264) is (spell:227338), she will regenerate 2% of her health every second. When (npc:114264) reaches full health, (npc:114262) will leap back into the saddle and re-enter Phase 1. This takes 25 seconds.<br/><br/>In all future mounted phases, (npc:114264) gains a new ability, (spell:227365).<br/><br/>This cycle repeats until (npc:114262) is slain. When this happens, (npc:114264) will (spell:228895), taking and dealing 100% more damage. During this brief final phase of the fight, (npc:114264) will only use the (spell:227363) ability.| |DPS|<b>Save DPS cooldowns for the (npc:114262) phase, since (npc:114264) will regenerate her health anyway<br/><br/>During Phase 1:<br/><br/><b>Whenever (spell:227404) is cast, check to see if you have the ghostly apparition attached to your character model, and tell your healer if so<br/><b>Caster DPS should stop casting as (spell:227363) is about to complete, to avoid being interrupted<br/><b>Move out of (spell:227365), and duck behind the horses that have just passed to minimize movement<br/><br/>During Phase 2:<br/><br/><b>Use DPS cooldowns here to take a bigger chunk out of (npc:114262)'s health pool<br/><b>Ranged DPS should stack up on the pre-assigned stack point<br/><b>Side-step out of (spell:227339)<br/><b>Avoid being in front of (npc:114262) when (spell:227493) is being cast<br/><b>Melee DPS must stack on the stac