fensive cooldown for each (spell:228852)| 
|BOSSID|114247| |LVL|110| |NAME|The Curator| |MAPID|1115| |ST|This encounter is a two-phase fight. The first phase is mostly about killing adds and avoiding mechanics, while the second phase is a burn phase on the boss. Players should save their DPS cooldowns for the burn phases, which occur approximately every minute.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Actively Attacking<br/><br/>The first phase of the encounter, the adds phase, lasts until (npc:114247) spends all of his mana. This takes approximately 55 seconds (40 seconds to deplete his mana, and a 15 second delay before he enters Phase 2).<br/><br/>Twice during the phase - once at the very start, and again 12 seconds later - (npc:114247) will cast (spell:227267).<br/><br/>Every 12-15 seconds, (npc:114247) will cast (spell:227465).<br/><br/>Tanks should pull (npc:114247) to the near end of the hallway, with the party spread out along the wall behind him. Move (npc:114247) just enough that no players have to stand in the (spell:227465) pools in order to attack the boss.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Regenerating Mana<br/><br/>About 15 seconds after (npc:114247) reaches 0 mana, he will cast (spell:227254).<br/><br/>At the end of each (spell:227254) cast, (npc:114247) will cast (spell:227257), dealing moderate Arcane damage to all players.<br/><br/>This also acts as a soft enrage mechanic; players must defeat (npc:114247) before (spell:227257) damage becomes fatal.| |DPS|<b>Quickly swap to and kill the (npc:114249) adds as they spawn<br/><b>Save DPS cooldowns for the (spell:227254) phase, while (npc:114247) takes additional damage<br/><b>Move out of pools of (spell:227465), but stay close to existing pools to save space<br/><b>Stay spread out to reduce splash damage from (spell:228738)<br/><b>Use a defensive CD for high-stack (spell:227257) casts| |HEAL|<b>Phase 1 damage is spiky and random<br/><b>Be sure to top players off before and after each (spell:227257), using raid CDs if necessary<br/><b>Contribute damage on (npc:114247) during (spell:227254) when possible<br/><b>Move out of pools of (spell:227465)<br/><b>Stay spread out to reduce splash damage from (spell:228738)<br/><b>Use a defensive cd for higher-stack (spell:227257) casts| |TANK|<b>Move (npc:114247) each time he casts (spell:227465)<br/><b>Help kill nearby (npc:114249) adds<br/><b>Save offensive cooldowns for the (spell:227254) phase<br/><b>Use AM/CDs whenever adds are active or for higher-stack (spell:227257) casts| 
|BOSSID|114895| |LVL|110| |NAME|Nightbane| |MAPID|1115| |ST|Summoning (npc:114895)<br/><br/>(npc:114895) is a secret, summonable boss in the lower half of the Return to Karazhan dungeon. Players must first complete a time trial by clicking all five of the (npc:115013) before their time runs out:<br/><b>Upon opening the door after zoning into Karazhan, the following emote happens: "The strange chill of a dark presence winds through the air." This starts the timer.<br/><b>The party must click the first crystal, in the Opera Hall audience in front of the stage, within 8 minutes. This requires defeating the Opera Hall encounter and killing a substantial amount of trash backstage, in the pit, and in the audience.<br/><b>After the first crystal you will gain a buff, (spell:229074), with a 6min duration. This is now your timer. As you click crystals, it will add a stacking buff and 5 minutes to the time you had left on your buff.<br/><b>The (npc:115013)s are located: 1 in the audience from Opera, 1 in the room on the left just before (npc:113971) (you dont need to kill her), 1 after you kill (npc:114312), 1 in the Spider Room (then you click the portal to the stairway), 1 after you kill (npc:114247).<br/><b>If you click all the (npc:115013)s within the allotted time, after (npc:114247), you run back to (npc:114895)'s room and (npc:115038) is there and he summons (npc:114895).<br/><b>When you speak to (npc:115038) you get the (aid:11430) achievement.<br/><b>Once all crystals are clicked in the allotted time, your timer buff will change to (spell:229077) and you will have 5 minutes to go speak with (npc:115038) and summon (npc:114895). The original Roleplay upon summoning (npc:114895) will play.<br/><b>Once you speak to (npc:115038) and (npc:114895) is summoned, you are able to wipe without worry. He will still be there and shout at you as he continuously slays you.<br/><br/>The (npc:114895) encounter is a primarily single-target fight with three phases. Small adds are spawned every 20 seconds during Phases 1 and 3, and approximately every 10 seconds during Phase 2, but if the encounter is executed appropriately, there will only be 1-2 adds each time.<br/><br/>Throughout the entire encounter, (npc:114895) will cast (spell:228808), targeting a random player and firing a projectile at their feet.<br/><br/>(npc:114895) cycles through three phases during the encounter: two ground phases, and one air phase. The final ground phase is the most difficult part of the encounter, so players should save (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) for this part of the fight.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Ground Phase<br/><br/>Begin the fight with (npc:114895) at one end of the Master's Terrace.<br/><br/>The mechanic with the most wipe potential is (spell:228796), a debuff that (npc:114895) will cast on a random non-tank target every 25 seconds.<br/><br/>The party must also manage the (spell:228829) debuff, which (npc:114895) will apply to a random non-tank target approximately every 20 seconds.<br/><br/>The (npc:114906) that this spell summons are fairly trivial mobs, dealing only melee damage. However, when they die, they detonate with (spell:228833).<br/><br/>Every 12 seconds, (npc:114895) will attempt to cast (spell:229307).<br/><br/>Periodically, (npc:114895) will buff himself with (spell:228790) or (spell:228792).<br/><br/>Finally, (npc:114895) will attack the tank with (spell:228785) approximately every 23 seconds.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Air Phase<br/><br/>When (npc:114895) reaches 50% health, he will fly into the air and cast (spell:228839), summoning a large skeletal golem from a plume of Shadowflame. (These flames do not deal damage to players.) <br/><br/>The golem, (npc:114903), has approximately 63 million health. (npc:114895) remains airborne until (npc:114903) has been defeated.<br/><br/>(npc:114903) has a single ability, (spell:228835), that he will cast on a random target every 20 seconds.<br/><br/>During this phase, (npc:114895) will no longer use (spell:228829), (spell:228785), (spell:228790), (spell:228796), or (spell:228792). He will continue to create (spell:228808) beneath a random target's feet, and increases the frequency to every 12 seconds. In addition, he gains a new ability, (spell:228834).<br/><br/>In addition, (npc:114895) will frequently summon a (npc:114906) add every 8-10 seconds. Like the (npc:114906) in Phase 1, these are fairly trivial mobs that deal light melee damage and detonate upon death with (spell:228833). Space out their deaths so that the tank does not gain too many stacks of (spell:228833) while also dealing with (npc:114903)'s damage.<br/><br/>Continue kiting (npc:114903) in the same fashion as (npc:114895), to keep the (spell:228808) pools under control. It is possible to begin doubling back if necessary, since the (spell:228808) patches from the start of Phase 1 should have despawned by the middle of Phase 2.<br/><br/>Phase 3: Ground Phase<br/><br/>When (npc:114903) is defeated, (npc:114895) will land and resume using his ground phase abilities. He also gains one new ability, (spell:228837).<br/><br/>Any players with a fear immunity should use it in advance of the first (spell:228837), in hopes of defeating (npc:114895) before the second cast.<br/><br/>Other than this mechanic, Phase 3 plays out with the same timers and mechanics as Phase 1, but with the added damage from (spell:228834) stacks that have carried over from the previous phase. Healers should use their strongest CDs to deal with Phase 3 damage.| |DPS|<b>Save cooldowns for phase 3 to align with (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353)<br/><b>Use a defensive cooldown if targeted by (spell:228829), to make its damage survivable<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:229307) when possible<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:228796), step into a patch of (spell:228808) to lower your health, so its detonation deals trivial damage<br/><b>Quickly kill the (npc:114906) as they spawn, and use CC or AoE stuns to keep them under control<br/><b>During phase 2, kill (npc:114906) with passive cleave/AoE while primarily attacking (npc:114903)<br/><b>Time your cooldowns in Phase 3 around the (spell:228837) mechanic<br/><b>Do not stand in front or behind of (npc:114895), to avoid (spell:228785) and (spell:228787)<br/><b>Move out of (spell:228808) patches as they spawn| |HEAL|<b>Unless it will save the player's life, do not dispel (spell:228829) above one stack<br/><b>The party will take heavy AoE damage from (spell:228792)<br/><b><br/><b>The tank takes very heavy damage, especially during (spell:228790) or when debuffed by (spell:228833)<br/><b>Do not heal the player with (spell:228796) - let their health drop low so its detonation deals trivial damage to the rest of the party<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:228796), stand in the nearest (spell:228808) patch to lower your health<br/><b>Quickly swap to and heal the player targeted by (spell:228835)<br/><b>During Phase 3, be sure the tank is topped off for each (spell:228837), and apply HoTs/absorbs/external cooldowns as necessary<br/><b>Use your strongest CDs in Phase 3, as the combination of (spell:228796)/(spell:228792)/(spell:228834) DoT can be fatal<br/><b>Do not stand in front or behind of (npc:114895), to avoid (spell:228785) and (spell:228787)<br/><b>Move out of (spell:228808) patches as they spawn| |TANK|<b>Move (npc:114895) away from nearby patches of (spell:228808), but go slowly to conserve space<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation or a cooldown for (spell:228785) damage<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation or a cooldown when (npc:114895) gains (spell:228790), especially if you have stacks of (spell:228833)<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:229307) when possible<br/><b>Pick up the (npc:114906) that spawn when (spell:228829) drops off or during phase 2<br/><b>Move (npc:114903) away from (spell:228808) patches as they spawn<br/><b>During Phase 3, use a cooldown just before the (spell:228837) cast completes| 
|BOSSID|114350| |LVL|110| |NAME|Shade of Medivh| |MAPID|1115| |ST|This encounter is primarily single-target, and requires frequent interupts and moderate to heavy movement.<br/><br/>The (npc:114350) will gradually gain mana over the course of 30 seconds, while attacking the party with three spells:<br/><br/>The (npc:114350) casts these spells in completely random order, varying each time he is pulled, and he may cast the same spell back-to-back multiple times. It is not possible to assign one player to interrupt every instance of one spell.<br/><br/>Good communication is necessary to avoid overlapping interrupt abilities. Players should consider macroing a '/say Interrupted!' into their own interrupt mechanics so that other party members are aware and can set an interrupt order. Voice chat is another option for communicating the interrupt order.<br/><br/>The party should stay spread out just far enough that (spell:227615) does not splash its damage normally, but close enough that players can react quickly to (spell:227592)/(spell:227615) mechanics.<br/><br/>Upon reaching full mana, the (npc:114350) will dump his entire mana bar to cast an "ultimate" ability, chosen randomly each time from three possibilities:<br/><br/>The (spell:227779) ultimate will fill the room with a powerful blizzard, coating the floor in ice.<br/><br/>If the (npc:114350) chooses to use the (spell:228269) ultimate, he will surround two players with (spell:228269) rings.<br/><br/>If the (npc:114350) casts (spell:228334) as his ultimate ability, he will disappear, splitting his essence into three (npc:114675) adds at the edges of the room.<br/><br/>The fight cycles through the mana-regeneration phase and the ultimate abilities until players have defeated the (npc:114350). The difficulty comes from remembering how to handle all of the abilities and reacting quickly to randomized cast sequences.| |DPS|<b>Spread out to avoid splashing (spell:227615) damage or overlapping (spell:228269) circles<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:227628) and (spell:227592) when possible, but communicate so that other players do not waste their interrupt cooldowns<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:227615) and another player is in (spell:227592), move to them to free them<br/><b>During (spell:228334), attack (npc:114675)s and use defensive CDs when your stacks of (spell:228524) are high<br/><b>During (spell:227779), continually move or jump to keep the (spell:227779) stacks low<br/><b>During (spell:228269), do not leave your own (spell:228269) if targeted, and do not enter another player's (spell:228269)| |HEAL|<b>The tank may require heavy healing for (spell:227628) casts, especially if they are interrupted late in the cast<br/><b>If a (spell:227628) cast finishes, the tank may require an external cooldown during the (spell:227644) debuff<br/><b>Players struck by (spell:227615) will need focused healing due to the DoT effect<br/><b>Top up players in (spell:227592) so they will survive the hit from (spell:227615) to free them<br/><b>Use a raid CD during (spell:228334)<br/><b>Use mobility CDs and mobile healing CDs or abilities during (spell:227779)<br/><b>During (spell:227779), continually move or jump to keep the (spell:227779) stacks low<br/><b>During (spell:228269), do not leave your own (spell:228269) if targeted, and do not enter another player's (spell:228269)| |TANK|<b>Interrupt (spell:227628) when possible, but communicate so that other players do not waste their interrupt cooldowns<br/><b>Use a strong CD if you gain the (spell:227644) debuff<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:227615) and a nearby player is in (spell:227592), move to them to free them<br/><b>During (spell:228334), attack (npc:114675)s and use defensive CDs when your stacks of (spell:228524) are high<br/><b>During (spell:227779), continually move or jump to keep the (spell:227779) stacks low<br/><b>During (spell:228269), do not leave your own (spell:228269) if targeted, and do not enter another player's (spell:228269)| 
|BOSSID|114252| |LVL|110| |NAME|Mana Devourer| |MAPID|1115| |ST|This encounter is a single-target fight with high movement and awareness requirements. <br/><br/>The primary objective of the encounter is to prevent the (npc:114252) from reaching 100% mana. If the (npc:114252) does reach full mana, it will cast (spell:227507), wiping the party.<br/><br/>When a player absorbs a sphere of (spell:227296), they will recover 10% of their mana pool and gain a stack of (spell:227502).<br/><br/>Note that, the more (spell:227296) spheres the party lets through, the more (spell:227296) spheres will be generated by the next (spell:227297).<br/><br/>(spell:227502) has no duration, but players can remove it by stepping into an (spell:227523), which the (npc:114252) will create every 20 seconds throughout the fight.<br/><br/>Players with 3+ stacks of (spell:227502) should remove them by stepping into an (spell:227523).<br/><br/>In addition to these mechanics, the (npc:114252) will also attack the party with (spell:227618) and (spell:227457).<br/><br/>The (npc:114252) fight is somewhat of a DPS check, given that most groups will not find it possible to soak all (spell:227296) spheres, so the (npc:114252)'s mana total will slowly approach 100%. Despite the (spell:227502) buff dealing additional damage, the best use for (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) is probably at the beginning of the encounter, for 30 seconds of largely uninterrupted damage.| |DPS|<b>Use DPS cooldowns at the start for 30 seconds of uninterrupted, low-movement damage<br/><b>Move out of (spell:227618) and (spell:227523) pools<br/><b>When (npc:114252) creates (spell:227296) orbs, intercept them before they reach the boss<br/><b>When all the (spell:227296) orbs have been collected or reabsorbed, run into an (spell:227523) to drop your (spell:227502) stacks<br/><b>Use a defensive CD while dropping (spell:227502) stacks, particularly if you have more than 2-3 stacks of it| |HEAL|<b>Top players up before and after (spell:227457)<br/><b>Players with more stacks of (spell:227502) will require more healing<br/><b>Use raid CDs to deal with the party damage of using (spell:227523)s to drop (spell:227502) stacks<br/><b>Intercept (spell:227296) before it reaches the boss<br/><b>When all the (spell:227296) orbs have been collected or reabsorbed, run into an (spell:227523) to drop your (spell:227502) stacks<br/><b>Use a defensive CD while dropping (spell:227502) stacks, particularly if you have more than 2-3 stacks of it| |TANK|<b>Avoid standing in (spell:227618) or (spell:227523) pools<br/><b>Try to move (npc:114252) as little as possible<br/><b>But if unsoaked (spell:227296) is approaching, pull (npc:114252) away from it to give the party more time to soak the orbs<br/><b>If you soak (spell:227296) and gain (spell:227502) stacks, use stronger cooldowns until you can get to an (spell:227523) pool| 
|BOSSID|114790| |LVL|110| |NAME|Viz'aduum the Watcher| |MAPID|1115| |ST|This encounter is a hectic, complicated, three-phase fight that is primarily single-target. Heavy movement, high DPS, interrupts, and strong awareness of surroundings are required.<br/><br/>This encounter takes place in Netherspace, encompassing the outdoor platform on which players originally faced (npc:15690) in the Karazhan raid, as well as the two Legion Command Ships hovering overhead.<br/><b>When (npc:114790) reaches 66% health remaining, he will summon a (spell:229610) and escape to the nearest Legion Command Ship. Players may take this (spell:229610) to pursue him, and enter phase 2 of the fight.<br/><b>At 33% health, (npc:114790) will summon another (spell:229610) to flee to the second Legion Command Ship, where he will attempt to open a portal to the Twisting Nether and allow a flow of Legion troops to invade Azeroth.<br/><b>Use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) at the start of the fight to quickly progress to Phase 2 and eliminate one of the mechanics of the fight. Phase 1 is very high in damage and movement, so making it shorter is likely to prevent more deaths than in any other phase.<br/><br/>Core Mechanics - All Phases<br/><br/>All three phases of the fight share three core mechanics.<br/><br/>(npc:114790) will frequently target a random player for (spell:229151), turning to face the player before beginning the cast.<br/><br/>Occasionally, (npc:114790) will target a random player with (spell:229159), applying a 10-second, dispellable debuff.<br/><br/>To deal with the (spell:229159) mechanic, the party should stay spread out around (npc:114790).<br/><br/>During phase 1, only one player will be affected with (spell:229159) on each cast. In subsequent phases, additional targets will be affected, meaning that the party will have to dodge multiple sets of (spell:229161) at the same time.<br/><br/>About every 5 seconds, as a filler between his other abilities, (npc:114790) will target the tank with (spell:229083).<br/><br/>To minimize (spell:229083) damage, players should:<br/><b>Assign the tank and one other trustworthy player to interrupt (spell:229083) casts<br/><b>It is likely impossible to interrupt every (spell:229083) cast, so don't plan to try<br/><b>When the tank has 2 stacks of (spell:229083), the tank should interrupt the next (spell:229083) cast<br/><b>The other player assigned to this task should interrupt the cast after that<br/><b>This should give the (spell:229083) DoT enough time to expire<br/><b>Most interrupt abilities should be back off cooldown by the time the tank reaches 2 stacks of (spell:229083) again<br/><b>Keep this interrupt rotation up for the entire fight<br/><b>If there is a mistake and the tank reaches 3 or more stacks of (spell:229083), the healer should dispel<br/><b>In each phase, (npc:114790) will also gain some unique mechanics that do not carry over to the next phase.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Netherspace<br/><br/>During Phase 1, (npc:114790) will call upon both of the Legion Command ships to assist him in defeating the party.<br/><br/>The first Legion Command Ship will fire a (spell:229248) when called upon. This occurs approximately every 40 seconds<br/><br/>Players targeted by (spell:229241)/(spell:229248) should move to the side of the platform before the (spell:229248) begins. Once the (spell:229248) has locked on, the targeted player should run to stay ahead of the (spell:229248) and avoid both (spell:229248) and (spell:229250) damage. This should ensure all (spell:229250) spawn in out-of-the-way locations and will not affect the rest of the party.<br/><br/>The second Legion Command Ship will bombard the encounter area with (spell:229287) when called upon, which will first occur 30 seconds into phase 1.<br/><br/>Phase 1 lasts until (npc:114790) reaches 66% health, at which time he will create a (spell:229610) and teleport to the first Legion Command Ship.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Command Ship<br/><br/>During this phase, (npc:114790) loses access to (spell:229248) (since the Command Ship will not attack itself). However, he retains (spell:229287), which he will use every 20 seconds. This is more dangerous on the Command Ship's deck, as space is more limited.<br/><br/>When (npc:114790) lands on the Command Ship, he will begin to cast (spell:229151) repeatedly until players, who land on the opposite end of the deck, engage him.<br/><br/>The sides of the Command Ship deck are fortified with four Legion Soul Harvesters, each of which fires fel lightning in a short radius from its position.<br/><br/>Once players reach (npc:114790), they do not have to worry about Legion Soul Harvesters anymore, and can focus on dodging (spell:229287) and handling the core mechanics of the fight.<br/><br/>Note that during Phase 2, (spell:229159) will affect 2 targets each time it is applied. Healers should dispel one target quickly, and let the second debuff expire, so that players are not dodging two waves of (spell:229161) at once.<br/><br/>When (npc:114790) reaches 30% health, he will summon another (spell:229610) and teleport to the deck of the final Legion Command Ship.<br/><br/>Phase 3: The Rift!<br/><br/>When (npc:114790) reaches the second Legion Command Ship, he will begin to cast (spell:230084), which has a 30-second cast time.<br/><br/>The only obstacle to reaching (npc:114790) in time to interrupt (spell:230084) is that the deck of the second Command Ship is lined with 6 (npc:115730) adds.<br/><br/>Even if players interupt the (spell:230084) cast, waves of 2 (npc:115730) adds will continue to spawn every 25 seconds. The first wave of these will appear shortly after players engage (npc:114790), and should be killed. Players can determine whether they need to kill the next set or can safely focus the boss.<br/><br/>(npc:114790) will use neither (spell:229287) nor (spell:229248) during this phase, so players must only handle the core mechanics.<br/><br/>Note that (spell:229159) will affe