|BOSSID|101950| |LVL|110| |NAME|Mindflayer Kaahrj| |MAPID|1066| |ST|(npc:101950) is an homage to the Faceless enemies players faced in Ulduar. This encounter is characterized by frequent spawns of a large number of adds, and players must ration their time between dealing enough boss damage to complete the fight and killing enough adds to survive the fight.<br/><br/>Approximately 30 seconds into the fight, and about every 40 seconds thereafter, (npc:101950) will cast (spell:201153), summoning (npc:101994)s placed randomly around the room.<br/><br/>Killing every (npc:101994) is not necessary; some may spawn up on balconies or other inconvenient places, and depending on your healer's strength, these can be left alive in favor of dealing damage to (npc:101950).<br/><br/>Note: Using one of the Crystal Defense System sconces for each (spell:201153) cast will deal with this mechanic quickly, instantly killing the (npc:101994) so players do not have to expend any DPS on them. However, it does leave the party with fewer Defense System charges for emergency uses.<br/><br/>Periodically, (npc:101950) will fire a (spell:197783) missile at a random non-tank player. These missiles arc slowly through the air and then land at the marked location.<br/><br/>Additionally, (npc:101950) will occasionally cast (spell:201146), targeting a random DPS player and causing them to flee in fear for 6 seconds. This is a physical-school fear effect and cannot be dispelled. Players must interrupt (spell:201146) each time it is cast.<br/><br/>Tanks must cope with (npc:101950)'s frequent (spell:201148) casts, which deal heavy Shadow damage and come approximately every 12-15 seconds, as well as very heavy melee damage since (npc:101950) strikes twice with most melee attacks. Consider using defensive cooldowns when (npc:101994)s have recently spawned, so the healer can focus on party healing.| |DPS|<b>Interrupt (spell:201146) when possible<br/><b>Kill nearby (npc:101994)s when they spawn<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:197783), move away from its impact point, and try to avoid standing in the remaining energy field<br/><b>Use a personal damage-reduction cooldown if several (npc:101994)s are targeting you with (spell:201153)| |HEAL|<b>The tank will likely need strong healing after each (spell:201148) cast<br/><b>Use healing cooldowns shortly after the (npc:101994)s spawn, when the party is taking the most damage from (spell:201153)<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:197783), move away from its impact point, and try to avoid standing in the remaining energy field<br/><b>Use a personal damage-reduction cooldown if several (npc:101994)s are targeting you with (spell:201153)| |TANK|<b>Drag (npc:101950) down the stairs to the main floor to allow players to reach more (npc:101994)s and have more space to dodge (spell:197783)<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation to reduce (spell:201148) damage<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:201146) when possible<br/><b>Move (npc:101950) closer to nearby (npc:101994)s so melee DPS can kill them easily<br/><b>Move away from nearby (spell:197783) locations to avoid the (spell:197783) debuff| 
