|BOSSID|104415| |LVL|110| |NAME|Chronomatic Anomaly| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This fight requires players to burst down priority targets about every minute, and then to quickly kill a small handful of mobs. The encounter has moderate to heavy movement requirements and requires interrupts and AoE CC for the small mob spawns.<br/><br/>The Nightwell has distorted the (spell:205653) in the areas around it, causing fluctuation in the speed at which time passes. This mechanic breaks the fight into phases, each one characterized by the speed of time:<br/><b>(spell:207012) has no effect on players, and is the phase that the fight will begin in<br/><b>(spell:207011) slows the rate of time by 30%, causing players to move and attack 30% slower, and also affecting cooldown recovery rate<br/><b>(spell:207013) increases the rate of time by 30%, causing players to move and attack 30% faster, and also affecting cooldown recovery rate<br/><br/>(spell:207011) and (spell:207013) also affect the abilities that (npc:104415) will cast. These differences will be mentioned in each spell's specific section in this guide.<br/><br/>The fight is unique in that (npc:104415) will use these abiilities in a different order on each difficulty. Even within the same difficulty, (npc:104415) will use his abilities at different times and in different orders in each phase. Because of this, there is no real way to list most of the spell cooldowns and frequencies here; consult a boss mod if you require more details on timing.<br/><br/>The first four phases are triggered by using the (spell:212115)/(spell:219823) interaction; the time speed will shift immediately when the tank interrupts (spell:219823). Subsequent phases become uncoupled from this interaction, making the fight feel very unpredictable.<br/><br/>After 7 minutes, (npc:104415) will enrage and cast (spell:207976), if he isn't dead by this point the raid will wipe very quickly.<br/><br/>Occasionally, a (npc:104676) will spill out of the Nightwell and spawn an add. The (npc:104676) is a priority DPS target, and the raid should switch to it quickly.<br/><br/>Note that during (spell:207013), (npc:104676)s are very likely to successfully cast (spell:207228). Healers may wish to use CDs during this time to help the raid survive.<br/><br/>When a (npc:104676) dies, it will spawn 4 (npc:114671)s at its location.<br/><br/>A minute into each of the first four phases, and occasionally thereafter, (npc:104415) will turn to the Nightwell and begin to channel (spell:219823) from it.<br/><br/>(spell:212076)s are spawned whenever a (npc:104676) is killed.<br/><br/>It is important to kill (npc:104676)s as quickly as possible, so that the (spell:212076) forms with enough time to interrupt (spell:219823).<br/><br/>In some phases, (npc:104676)s spawn late, leaving little time between the time it spawns and the time that (npc:104415) channels his (spell:219823). Healers should use CDs to help survive the initial (spell:219823) ticks until the (spell:212115) ability can be used.<br/><br/>For 15 seconds after the (spell:212115) is used, (npc:104415) takes 30% increased damage. Players should save their DPS cooldowns for these moments. <br/><br/>(spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) may be best used to help quickly burn down a late-spawning (npc:104676), and then to deal additional damage to (npc:104415) while he is vulnerable.<br/><br/>Periodically, (npc:104415) will choose a random player and plant a (spell:206617) on them.<br/><br/>Players affected by (spell:206617) should run away from the raid when their debuff is close to expiring, to reduce the damage dealt.<br/><br/>The duration of the (spell:206617) debuff is random, but is affected by the (spell:205653).<br/><br/>Targeted players should wait until they have less than 8 seconds left on their debuff before running out; when this debuff is applied during the (spell:207013) phase, they should run out immediately. The (spell:206617) debuff will cause a frequent pulsing effect at the player's feet when it is nearing expiration, to help you remember to run!<br/><br/>(spell:206612) is a simple mechanic; (npc:104415) will mark the floor at several random players' feet, and then launch a projectile at those locations. This occurs in three rapid waves, and each wave consists of 5 projectiles.<br/><br/>Players should move away in order to avoid taking damage from the (spell:206612). The phase of the fight determines how long players have to dodge these projectiles<br/><br/>Once or twice per phase, (npc:104415) will cause (spell:205707) to spill from the Nightwell. Several waves of projectiles will be emitted from the Nightwell and fly outward in straight lines to the edge of the room. Players who stand in (spell:205707) will take moderate damage. This can quickly add up to fatal damage if players are struck by several (spell:205707) in a short window of time.<br/><br/>The speed at which the (spell:205707) move is dictated by the (spell:205653), with (spell:207011) causing extremely slow orbs and (spell:207013) causing extremely fast ones.<br/><br/>In addition, the waves themselves move at different speeds, so there will sometimes be places in the room where the (spell:205707) present an unbroken line and players will be unable to dodge all of them. This position is different in each phase.<br/><br/>Avoid as many (spell:205707) as possible. During the (spell:207013) phase, healers may wish to use cooldowns to help the raid survive, as many of the orbs may be moving too quickly to easily dodge.<br/><br/>During each phase, (npc:104415) will debuff players with (spell:206609). This applies a healing absorption shield to the targeted players.<br/><br/>The number of targets, frequency of cast, size of the absorption shield, and duration of the debuff are all dependent upon the (spell:205653).<br/><br/>(npc:104415) will afflict his current target with (spell:206607) every 5-6 seconds. This is the tank-swap mechanic in the encounter.<br/><br/>The duration of (spell:206607) and the speed at which they tick is dependent upon the (spell:205653).<br/><br/>Phase changes may also alter existing (spell:206607) durations, increasing or decreasing the time remaining on the debuff.<br/><br/>During (spell:207011), tanks will likely need to take 9 stacks of the debuff before taunt swapping, and will be taking very heavy damage. Save heavy cooldowns for these times; healers should also be prepared to pay extra attention to tank healing.<br/><br/>(npc:104415) will not cast (spell:206607) while he is channelling (spell:219823), which can give tanks a break to reset stacks, especially during (spell:207011).| |DPS|<b>Save DPS cooldowns to help kill late-spawning (npc:104676)s or for the boss's vulnerability after each (spell:212115)<br/><b>Move toward the (npc:104676) when it begins to form<br/><b>Prioritize killing the (npc:104676) over dealing damage to (npc:104415)<br/><b>Quickly burst down the (npc:114671)s<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:207228) when possible<br/><b>Use AoE stuns and other CC to prevent (npc:114671)s from casting<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206617), run away from the raid when the debuff begins pulsating/has fewer than 8 seconds remaining<br/><b>Move away from (spell:206612) and (spell:205707) zones| |HEAL|<b>Use healing cooldowns whenever (npc:104415) begins channeling (spell:219823) before the (npc:104676) dies<br/><b>Use healing cooldowns during (spell:205707) in the (spell:207013) phase<br/><b>Use a minor healing cooldown during the whole-raid (spell:206609) that occurs during (spell:207011) phases<br/><b>Prioritize healing players with red (spell:206609) debuffs over those with yellow or green debuffs<br/><b>Heavy tank healing will be needed during (spell:207011) when the tanks reach high stacks of (spell:206607)<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206617), run away from the raid when the debuff begins pulsating/has fewer than 8 seconds remaining<br/><b>Move away from (spell:206612) and (spell:205707) zones| |TANK|<b>Taunt-swap the boss before either tank reaches 10 stacks of (spell:206607)<br/><b>Swap after 5-6 stacks during (spell:207012)<br/><b>Swap after 3 stacks during (spell:207013)<br/><b>Swap on 9 stacks during (spell:207011), and use cooldowns to survive<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation while tanking (npc:104415) with several stacks of (spell:206607)<br/><b>Move the boss over to the (npc:104676) for cleave and splash AoE damage<br/><b>When the (spell:212076) spawns, interact with it to gain (spell:212099)<br/><b>When (npc:104415) casts (spell:219823), the tank with (spell:212099) should approach the boss to interrupt it<br/><b>Interrupt (spell:207228) when possible<br/><b>Use AoE stuns and other CC to prevent (npc:114671)s from casting<br/><b>Move away from (spell:206612) and (spell:205707) zones| 
|BOSSID|104288| |LVL|110| |NAME|Trilliax| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This fight is a single-target fight that features frequent, often heavy, movement, and requires high raid awareness.<br/><br/>(npc:104288) will repeatedly cycle through three phases during the encounter: (spell:206560), (spell:206557), and (spell:206559), in that order. Some of (npc:104288)'s abilities are phase-independent, and will be used across multiple phases, but each of the three phases also introduces mechanics that are unique to that phase.<br/><br/>Phase-Independent Abilities<br/><br/><b>Damaging (npc:104288) causes pools of (spell:206488) to form at random players' locations. DPS and healer players are valid targets, but tanks do not appear to be. This will occur during all phases of the encounter.<br/><b>Tanks should pull (npc:104288) to the edge of the room and kite in a circle around the room when (spell:206488) becomes too dense for melee DPS to be able to fight comfortably. Ranged DPS and healers should stand behind the boss and move forward when necessary, still staying within the outer ring of the room. Try to avoid standing in the center of the room.<br/><b>(npc:104288) uses (spell:206641) during (spell:206560) and (spell:206557) phases, but not during (spell:206559) phase. This is a tank-swap mechanic.<br/><b>The time between (spell:206641)es depends upon the phase of the encounter.<br/><b>(npc:104288) cannot cast (spell:206641) while channeling (spell:207630), and will not attack players at all during (spell:206559) phase. This gives tanks and healers plenty of time to recover from (spell:206641) damage.<br/><br/>Phase 1: (spell:206560)<br/><br/><b>(spell:206560) phase lasts 45 seconds. <br/><b>The first (spell:206560) phase only uses one of its mechanics, because the other mechanics that (npc:104288) can use in this phase rely on events that occur in (spell:206559) phase. Since there are fewer mechanics, and since all phase transitions are timed, this is an excellent place to use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353).<br/><b>During these first 45 seconds of the fight, players will primarily deal with (npc:104288)'s phase-independent abilities and a single (spell:206560) mechanic: (spell:215062).<br/><b>It is important to try to eat all of the (spell:215062) cakes during (spell:206560) phase, because it is otherwise a low-damage phase.<br/><br/>Phase 2: (spell:206557)<br/><br/><b>(spell:206557) phase lasts 40 seconds.<br/><b>Every second, (npc:104288) will damage random targets with (spell:206645).<br/><b>At the start of (spell:206557) phase, (npc:104288) will link two players together with (spell:208910).<br/><b>Approximately 24 seconds into the phase, (npc:104288) will leap into the center of the room and begin to cast (spell:207630).<br/><b>(spell:207630) is likely to be deadly to any player who reacts slowly or moves in the wrong direction, especially in combination with (spell:206645). Always watch where (npc:104288) is facing when it leaps to the center of the room.<br/><b>If the raid has been careful with its positioning, the center of the room will be clear of (spell:206488) during the start of (spell:207630). However, the boss will still create (spell:206488) pools during (spell:207630). It is more important to avoid (spell:207630) damage than to avoid passing through (spell:206488) pools, but ideally players should avoid both.<br/><br/>Phase 3: (spell:206559)<br/><br/><b>(spell:206559) phase lasts 12-13 seconds. During this phase, (npc:104288) is immobile and will not attack players directly.<br/><b>At the start of (spell:206559) phase, (npc:104288) will spawn a few (spell:207502)s at random locations in the room.<br/><b>Near the end of (spell:206559) phase, (npc:104288) will summon five (npc:104596)s with (spell:207513).<br/><b>Players with the (spell:207502) shield are ideal for the task of destroying (npc:104596)s. Wait for the red "bomb" icon to appear over the casting (npc:104596)'s head and leap onto it. On Normal mode, each (spell:207502) should prevent enough damage to soak multiple (spell:207328)s.<br/><b>If necessary, a player without (spell:207502) can destroy a casting (npc:104596), but should use a defensive cooldown to do so.<br/><br/>(spell:206560), Revisited<br/><br/><b>For the rest of the fight, (spell:206560) phase will exhibit two additional mechanics.<br/><b>Right at the transition between (spell:206559) and (spell:206560), (npc:104288) will (spell:214582) three players.<br/><b>The (spell:214582) pulse also affects (npc:104596)s, allowing them to consume more (spell:206488) pools before they explode.<br/><b>Players targeted by (spell:214582) should use the pulse to drain Mana from as many (npc:104596)s as possible, to allow the (npc:104596)s to clean more of the room and delay the (spell:207328) casts.<br/><b>It's unlikely that the (npc:104596)s will be able to remove every (spell:206488) pool before reaching full Mana and self-destructing, but using the (spell:214582) debuffs well can clear a lot of them, making the fight much easier.<br/><b>The only time you do not want to have a (spell:214582) player on a (npc:104596) is when the (npc:104596) is heading for a freshly spawned (spell:215062) cake.<br/><b>10 seconds into (spell:206560) phase, (npc:104288) will scan the room for any remaining (spell:215062) cakes. If there are any, (npc:104288) will destroy them with (spell:206820).<br/><b>To prevent (spell:206820), players must simply be sure to eat all (spell:215062) cakes that appear during the course of the fight. It is best to do this during (spell:206560) phase where damage is otherwise low.<br/><b>As in the first (spell:206560) phase, (npc:104288) will again summon two sets of (spell:215062) cakes, about 13 seconds and 43 seconds after the phase begins. This is after the (spell:206820) check, so these new (spell:215062) cakes will never trigger a (spell:206820) cast.| |DPS|<b>Use DPS cooldowns at the start of the fight with (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353)<br/><b>Avoid standing in the center of the room, so that (spell:206488) stays out of the middle<br/><b>Move out of (spell:206488) pools that spawn nearby<br/><b>Move away from (spell:215062) spawn points<br/><b>Consume (spell:215062)s during (spell:206560) phase, and use a defensive cooldown if you take 2 stacks<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:208910), find your partner and stand on them<br/><b>Avoid (spell:207630) damage by staying on (npc:104288)'s side<br/><b>Eat a (spell:207502) if assigned to do so, and destroy casting (npc:104596)s<br/><b>If targeted with (spell:214582), chase (npc:104596)s to drain their Mana<br/><b>If possible, stun (npc:104596)s if they are approaching (spell:215062) cakes| |HEAL|<b>Players with (spell:215062), (spell:206641), and (spell:214582) debuffs will require additional healing<br/><b>Use raid cooldowns during (spell:206557) phase, while (spell:206645) and (spell:215062) debuffs coexist or during (spell:207630)<br/><b>Use single-target cooldowns on tanks with 2 stacks of (spell:206641)<br/><b>Avoid standing in the center of the room, so that (spell:206488) stays out of the middle<br/><b>Move out of (spell:206488) pools that spawn nearby<br/><b>Move away from (spell:215062) spawn points<br/><b>Consume (spell:215062)s during (spell:206560) phase, and use a defensive cooldown if you take 2 stacks<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:208910), find your partner and stand on them<br/><b>Avoid (spell:207630) damage by staying on (npc:104288)'s side<br/><b>Eat a (spell:207502) if assigned to do so, and destroy casting (npc:104596)s<br/><b>If targeted with (spell:214582), chase (npc:104596)s to drain their Mana<br/><b>If possible, stun (npc:104596)s if they are approaching (spell:215062) cakes| |TANK|<b>At the start of each (spell:206560) phase, pull (npc:104288) to the edge of the encounter area<br/><b>Move (npc:104288) in a circle around the edge of the room to get away from (spell:206488)<br/><b>Stack together to split (spell:206641) damage<br/><b>Swap tanking duties after 2 (spell:206641) casts/debuffs<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation for each (spell:206641), and cooldowns for (spell:206641)es that occur while you have 2 stacks<br/><b>When (npc:104288) is using (spell:212492) or is in (spell:206559) phase, deal as much damage as possible<br/><b>Only eat (spell:215062) if absolutely necessary<br/><b>Avoid (spell:207630) damage by staying on (npc:104288)'s side<br/><b>Do not eat (spell:207502) - leave them for (npc:104596)-soakers!<br/><b>Only destroy casting (npc:104596)s if absolutely necessary, and use a cooldown| 
|BOSSID|107699| |LVL|110| |NAME|Spellblade Aluriel| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This encounter involves moderate movement and requires the infrequent killing of a handful of low-health adds (once every 1-1.5 minutes). The encounter has three phases, each of which follows the same general structure, but with different abilities based on the element (npc:107699) wields during that phase. She will cycle through all 3 phases over the course of 4 minutes, and then repeat until dead.<br/><br/>Phase Structure<br/><br/>The three phases that (npc:107699) cycles through are Frost, Fire, and Arcane<br/><br/>Although the outcome of the events is very different from phase to phase, the order of the events that occur is similar.<br/><br/>For a clearer depiction of how this works in each phase, check the phase description below.<br/><br/>Throughout the entire fight, (npc:107699) will attack the tanks with (spell:212492).<br/><br/>Phase 1: Master of Frost: <br/><br/>(spell:212587)<br/><br/><b>While (npc:107699) is buffed with (spell:216389), she gains the ability to cast (spell:212587). She will cast (spell:212587) on two players approximately 18 seconds into the fight.<br/><b>If two players who are affected by (spell:212587) come into contact with each other, they will explode, transfering the (spell:212587) debuffs to the two nearest players.<br/><br/>(spell:212530)<br/><br/><b>23 seconds after the first cast of (spell:212587), (npc:107699) will (spell:212530), casting 2 new (spell:212587) debuffs onto ranged players.<br/><b>The intended method of dealing with these debuffs is to continually pass them off to new players when the current targets' (spell:212647) stacks are high.<br/><br/>(spell:212734)<br/><br/><b>30 seconds after the (spell:212530), (npc:107699) will (spell:212734).<br/><b>Note that (spell:212734) does not remove existing (spell:212587) debuffs. Players must still cope with the (spell:212587) mechanics following this cast.<br/><br/>(spell:213853)<br/><br/><b>4 seconds after (spell:212734), (npc:107699) will cast (spell:213853). As long as there is at least one (spell:212736) patch, this ability will summon 4 (npc:107237) adds<br/><br/>Alternate Strategy: Immuning (spell:212587)<br/><br/>During beta testing, players were able to nullify this phase's mechanics by transferring the (spell:212587)s onto players with immunities, and then using those immunities to remove the debuff entirely.<br/><br/>This strategy allows for the original targets of (spell:212587) to remove their debuffs quickly, at low stacks of (spell:212647), and vastly reduces the healing requirements for the encounter.<br/><br/>If this is successfully completed for both sets of (spell:212587),<br/><br/><b>There will be no active (spell:212587) buffs when (npc:107699) casts (spell:212734)<br/><b>This means that there will be no (spell:212736) puddles<br/><b>When (npc:107699) casts (spell:213853), there will be no (npc:107237) adds<br/><b>This strategy will require your raid to have at least 4 immunities every 4 minutes, and needs a little coordination, but can massively simplify this segment of the fight.<br/><br/>It is unclear whether this is an intended strategy or whether (spell:212587) will persist through/be unaffected by immunities when the encounter goes live.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Master of Fire<br/><br/>(spell:213166)<br/><br/><b>While (npc:107699) is buffed with (spell:213867), she gains the ability to cast (spell:213166). 18 seconds into the phase, she will cast (spell:213166) on a randomly chosen, non-tank target.<br/><b>(spell:213166) deals strong immediate damage, and leaves a (spell:213166) DoT that lasts for 26 seconds.<br/><br/>Replicate: (spell:213182)<br/><br/><b>Immediately after the charge, four copies of (npc:107699) will spawn at the targeted player's location. (npc:107699) and the 4 copies will each cast a (spell:213166) warning debuff on a randomly chosen target<br/><b>The (spell:213166) debuff can stack, so if the player targeted by the original (spell:213166) is targeted again by Replicate: (spell:213182), they will gain 2 stacks of the debuff.<br/><b>The best way to deal with this debuff is to have players marked with (spell:213166) run to a side of the boss where there are no other players<br/><br/>(spell:213276)<br/><br/><b>(npc:107699) will cast (spell:213276) about 48 seconds into the phase, while all players targeted by (spell:213166) are still affected by the (spell:213166) DoT.<br/><b>After the second set of (spell:213166) charges, the targeted players should stay in position and spread out to limit splashing (spell:213276) damage on one another or the rest of the raid. Once the (spell:213278) has formed, these players can move back into melee range.<br/><br/>(spell:213567)<br/><br/><b>Just over a minute into the phase, (npc:107699) will cast (spell:213567), summoning 6 (npc:107285)s from the (spell:213278) patches.<br/><b>There are 20 seconds before the end of the phase, and it is ideal for the (npc:107285)s to be dead by the start of Phase 3. Use burst AoE DPS here to quickly kill them.<br/><br/>Phase 3: Master of the Arcane<br/><br/>(spell:213520)<br/><br/><b>While (npc:107699) is buffed by (spell:213869), she gains the ability to cast (spell:213520). She will do so immediately upon entering Phase 3.<br/><b>If the raid is still stacked up at the start of Phase 3, the (spell:213520) may deal significant damage. Once Phase 3 begins - or ideally, when the (npc:107285) adds die - the ranged should spread out in preparation for (spell:213520)s.<br/><b>Once the (spell:213520) spawns, the whole raid should shift to be further from it, giving more time to react to (spell:213852).<br/><br/>(spell:213852)<br/><br/><b>15 seconds after summoning the first (spell:213520), (npc:107699) will cast (spell:213852).<br/><b>Moving at least 30 yards away from the (spell:213520)s once they have all spawned will give the raid more time to deal with the (spell:213390) mechanic. At this time, the raid should stack up.<br/><br/>(spell:213390)<br/><br/><b>20 seconds after casting (spell:213852), (npc:107699) will cast (spell:213390). This causes the (spell:213520)s to launch into the air and bombard the raid.<br/><b>Since there is a long flight time on the (spell:213520)s (depending upon your raid's distance from the orbs), it is best to wait for several of the targeting runes to form before the raid moves.<br/><b>Healers should use raid CDs to heal through the (spell:213390) damage.<br/><br/>(spell:213564)<br/><br/><b>About 20 seconds after beginning the (spell:213390) sequence - which works out to just a moment after the final (spell:213520) detonates - (npc:107699) will cast (spell:213564).<br/><br/>The phase will end 15 seconds after summoning the (npc:107287)s, but it is okay if some survive into the next phase, since there are 18 seconds before the first (spell:212587) will be cast.<br/><br/>At the end of the Arcane phase, or at the start of the next Frost phase, the ranged DPS should return to the original phase 1 positioning - behind the boss, spread out, at a distance to the melee DPS, and have a designated location for the (spell:212587) players to congregate.| |DPS|<b>Use burst AoE abilities and AoE CC to kill the (npc:107237)s, (npc:107285)s, and (npc:107287)s<br/><br/>During Frost phase,<br/><br/><b>Move to the designated area if targeted by (spell:212587)<br/><b>Use defensive cooldowns to survive higher stacks of (spell:212647)<br/><b>Run into another player with (spell:212587) when (spell:212647) stacks are too high<br/><b>Move away from the (spell:212587) area after you have transferred your debuff<br/><b>Move out of (spell:212736) patches following (spell:212734)<br/><br/>During Fire phase,<br/><br/><b>Stack up behind (npc:107699) unless you are still holding (spell:212587)<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:213166), move to (npc:107699)'s side, opposite the rest of the raid<br/><b>Spread out from other (spell:213166) targets to avoid knocking each other back<br/><b>After (spell:213276), move back into the raid<br/><br/>During Arcane phase,<br/><br/><b>Ranged DPS should spread out<br/><b>Move away from (spell:213520)s as they spawn<br/><b>Once all 8 have spawned, stack up on (npc:107699)<br/><b>Move away from (spell:213390) locations<br/><b>Never stand in front of (npc:107699), so you do not get affected by (spell:212492)| |HEAL|<b>Players with (spell:212587) and (spell:213166) debuffs will require additional healing<br/><b>Drop AoE effects on these players, and consider using cooldowns when the debuffs are on the maximum number of targets<br/><b>Tanks will need targeted healing for each (spell:212492) cast, every 33-47 seconds<br/><b>Use raid CDs during the (spell:213390) sequence, and minor CDs when adds are alive<br/><br/>During Frost phase,<br/><br/><b>Move to the designated area if targeted by (spell:212587)<br/><b>Use defensive cooldowns to survive higher stacks of (spell:212647)<br/><b>Run into another player with (spell:212587) when (spell:212647) stacks are too high<br/><b>Move away from the (spell:212587) area after you have transferred your debuff<br/><b>Move out of (spell:212736) patches following (spell:212734)<br/><br/>During Fire phase,<br/><br/><b>Stack up behind (npc:107699) unless you are still holding (spell:212587)<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:213166), move to (npc:107699)'s side, opposite the rest of the raid<br/><b>Spread out from other (spell:213166) targets to avoid knocking each other back<br/><b>After (spell:213276), move back into the raid<br/><br/>During Arcane phase,<br/><br/><b>Ranged DPS should spread out<br/><b>Move away from (spell:213520)s as they spawn<br/><b>Once all 8 have spawned, stack up on (npc:107699)<br/><b>Move away from (spell:213390) locations<br/><b>Never stand in front of (npc:107699), so you do not get affected by (spell:212492)| |TANK|<b>Both tanks should be in front of (npc:107699) at all times<br/><b>Taunt swap on 2 stacks of (spell:212494)<br/><b>Keep Active Mitigation up while (spell:212494) and tanking, or for each (spell:212492) when not tanking<br/><b>Avoid being close to players with (spell:212587) or (spell:213166) debuffs<br/><b>Drag (npc:107699) away from each (spell:213390) location to reduce damage taken<br/><b>Pull (npc:107699) away from ground effects ((spell:212736), (spell:213278), (spell:213504))<br/><b>Gather up the adds ((npc:107237), (npc:107285), (npc:107287)) for AoE| 
|BOSSID|103758| |LVL|110| |NAME|Star Augur Etraeus| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This encounter has four phases, each one triggered at a health percentage. As the first phase is essentially "the lack of a phase", where no unique mechanics occur, it will be called Phase 0 in this guide, and the remaining phases will be referred to as Phases 1-3.<br/><br/><b>Phase 0 lasts until (npc:103758) reaches 90% health<br/><b>Phase 1, the ice phase, lasts until (npc:103758) reaches 60% health<br/><b>Phase 2, the fel phase, lasts until (npc:103758) reaches 30% health<br/><b>Phase 3, the void phase, lasts from 30% until (npc:103758) is defeated<br/><br/>As the phases change, the walls of the Observatory will collapse and give players a glimpse into space, including a nearby planet and several nebulae. With each phase, these features take on a new appearance, making (npc:103758) one of the most visually stunning fights in the game.<br/><br/>The fight is single-target until the final phase, where large, priority-DPS adds will spawn about once per minute, and small groups of trivial minions spawn very frequently. This is the most difficult phase of the fight, and the raid should use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) here.<br/><br/>(npc:103758) does have a hard enrage mechanic in (spell:222761), a 10-second cast that instantly kills all players, but it is not yet known at what time he will cast this spell. In LFR testing, (npc:103758) began casting this at 7:45; however, longer logs from Normal and Heroic testing do not show (spell:222761) occurring at that time. (Edit: Normal reports show (spell:222761) occurring roughly 3 minutes into the phase.)<br/><br/>Phase 0: The Dome of Observation<br/><br/><b>This initial phase of the encounter introduces the raid to two concepts that will be reused, with thematic twists, in each subsequent phase of the fight.<br/><b>(npc:103758) will summon a sphere of light called a (npc:103790) near a random player. The (npc:103790) will hurl bolts of Fire at nearby players.<br/><b>Subsequent phases will have an Ejection mechanic that works similarly to this, with the spheres targeting and firing upon nearby players. The debuff that the Ejection mechanic gives will differ from phase to phase.<br/><b>Throughout the phase, (npc:103758) will frequently attack the current tank with (spell:205486).<br/><b>(npc:103758) will target the tanks with other "burst" mechanics through the rest of the fight, each one slightly different based on the phase of the fight.<br/><b>When (npc:103758) reaches 90% health, he will begin to cast (spell:221875). At the end of this cast, the Observatory walls will fall away and the fight will enter Phase 1.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Absolute Zero<br/><br/><b>In this phase, (npc:103758) will use Frost variations of his main abilities. He will also begin using (spell:205984), an ability that he will use in all remaining phases of the fight.<br/><b>(spell:205984) is a tank debuff that (npc:103758) will cast on his current target every 30 seconds.<br/><b>The (spell:206585) DoT has no duration. The DoT deals extremely heavy damage, and will stack if the tank tries to hold the DoT through multiple (spell:206577) events, which will quickly become unhealable. Tanks must use proximity to other players to remove the DoT as quickly as possible.<br/><b>In order to deal with this mechanic simply, mark a location in the room - along the edge of the platform - for the tank to run to for each (spell:206577).<br/><b>The rest of the raid should be divided into three groups, positioned on the left, right, and back sides of the boss.<br/><b>During this phase, (npc:103790) becomes (spell:206936). (npc:103758) will summon an icy sphere near a random player's location. The icy sphere will fire the (spell:206936) debuff at 3 nearby players.<br/><b>Because the raid is divided into groups, and the (spell:206936) sphere spawns near a player and affects the 3 nearest players, it is highly likely that all 3 (spell:206936) debuffs will affect players in the same group. This is why the 3-group strategy is only recommended for raids of 20+ players - if 3 in a group are out handling (spell:206936)/(spell:206938), the group will still be large enough to remove the tank's (spell:206585) debuff.<br/><b>(npc:103758) will cast (spell:206936) more frequently as the phase progresses, causing more and more of the raid to be dealing with this mechanic at once.<br/><b>This group of 3 (spell:206936) casts is the most difficult part of the phase, and healers should be prepared to use cooldowns as necessary.<br/><b>Finally, the tank-targeted (spell:205486) mechanic becomes (spell:206921) in this phase.<br/><b>When (npc:103758) reaches 60% health, he will begin to cast (spell:221875). The walls of the Observatory will seal, and then fall away again as the fight enters Phase 2.<br/><br/>Phase 2: A Shattered World<br/><br/><b>In this phase, (npc:103758) will use Fel variations of his main abilities.<br/><b>(npc:103790) in this phase becomes (spell:205649). (npc:103758) will summon a fel sphere near a random player's location, and this sphere will fire the (spell:205649) debuff at 3 nearby players.<br/><b>The raid should be loosely spread out in the center of the platform for this phase, and (spell:205649) targets should react quickly to avoid dropping (spell:206398) in the raid.<br/><b>(npc:103758) will cast (spell:205649) more frequently as the phase progresses, so that more and more of the raid will be dealing with this mechanic at once. The typical pattern is 4 (spell:205649), then a 10-second lull, then 3 more, then a 30-second lull, and then a rapid barrage of 5 (spell:205649) casts. The rapid barrage of 5 (spell:205649), meaning 15 (spell:205649) debuffs, is the most dangerous part of this phase.<br/><b>(spell:205984) will now summon a fel comet that deals (spell:206433) damage to the tank and all players within 5 yards. (npc:103758) will cast this ability every 30 seconds.<br/><b>Healers must be sure to top tanks up during the (spell:205984)/(spell:206433) cycle.<br/><b>Additionally, (npc:103758)'s (spell:205486) attack becomes (spell:206388) in this phase. (spell:206388) deals moderate damage on cast, and leaves a stacking DoT effect. Tanks should use heavier Active Mitigation and cooldowns while tanking with higher stacks of the DoT.<br/><b>When (npc:103758) reaches 30% health, he will begin to cast (spell:221875). The walls of the Observatory will seal, and then fall away again as the fight enters Phase 3.<br/><br/>Phase 3: Inevitable Fate<br/><br/><b>In this phase, (npc:103758) will use Shadow variations of his main abilities.<br/><b>(spell:205984) is cast every 65 seconds in this phase, and is not the primary tank-swap mechanic, although the off-tank should still taunt when the main tank is affected.<br/><b>The (npc:104880) will buff itself and (npc:103758) with (spell:207714) if it is too close to the boss, reducing their damage taken by 99%. To avoid this, the (spell:205984) tank should move to be just outside the blue circle in the center of the platform - this is far enough away to avoid (spell:207714), and is close enough that the DPS can quickly switch targets.<br/><b>The (npc:104880) will periodically cast (spell:207720), and is a priority DPS target<br/><b>The other tank-swap mechanic in this phase is (spell:214486), the Phase 3 version of (spell:205486).<br/><b>During this phase, (npc:103790) becomes (spell:207143). (npc:103758) will summon a shadowy sphere that will affect 2 nearby targets with (spell:207143).<br/><b>(npc:104688) adds are low-health, trivial mobs that can be easily handled with incidental AoE and cleave damage.<br/><b>In this final phase, the raid should stay stacked in the middle of the encounter area so that (npc:104688)s will all spawn together and so that healers can use their most efficient abilities to keep the raid alive.<br/><br/>After roughly 3 minutes on Normal mode, (npc:103758) will cast (spell:222761); this serves as a hard enrage as it kills the entire group.| |DPS|During Phase 1:<br/><br/><b>If targeted with (spell:206936), run to the edge of the platform away from other players to (spell:206938)<br/><b>Use a defensive cooldown as (spell:206936) expires<br/><b>At all other times, stand with your assigned group of players<br/><br/>During Phase 2:<br/><br/><b>Spread out in the middle of the platform<br/><b>Stay away from the tank marked with (spell:205984)<br/><b>When targeted by (spell:205649), run to the edge of the area, and keep moving to drop your (spell:206398) puddles<br/><b>Once (spell:205649) has ended, move back to a safe space near the middle, and stay spread out<br/><br/>During Phase 3:<br/><br/><b>Stack up behind (npc:103758)<br/><b>Use a defensive cooldown as (spell:207143) is about to expire<br/><b>Use AoE CC/stuns on the (npc:104688)s when they spawn<br/><b>All DPS must switch to the (npc:104880) immediately, and pool cooldowns/resources for it<br/><b>Use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) during this phase<br/><b>Turn away from the (npc:104880) when it casts (spell:207720)| |HEAL|During Phase 0:<br/><br/><b>Heal players affected by the  Coronal Ejection DoT<br/><br/>During Phase 1:<br/><br/><b>Top up players with the (spell:206936) debuff before it fades<br/><b>The tank with (spell:205984)/(spell:206585) will require heavy healing<br/><b>Use cooldowns to top the raid up after multiple waves of (spell:206936)/(spell:206938)<br/><b>If targeted with (spell:206936), run to the edge of the platform away from other players to (spell:206938)<br/><b>Use a defensive cooldown as (spell:206936) expires<br/><b>At all other times, stand with your assigned group of players<br/><br/>During Phase 2:<br/><br/><b>Both tanks will require heavy healing - at high stacks of (spell:206388), or during (spell:205984)/(spell:206433)<br/><b>Use cooldowns to recover from widespread (spell:205649) damage<br/><b>Spread out in the middle of the platform<br/><b>Stay away from the tank marked with (spell:205984)<br/><b>When targeted by (spell:205649), run to the edge of the area, and keep moving to drop your (spell:206398) puddles<br/><br/>During Phase 3:<br/><br/><b>Stack up behind (npc:103758)<br/><b>Use efficient AoE abilities to heal through the spreading (spell:214486) DoT<br/><b>Chain cooldowns as the raid's (spell:214486) stacks get higher<br/><b>Face away from the (npc:104880) when it casts (spell:207720)| |TANK|<b>Taunt-swap (npc:103758) each time the current tank gains (spell:205984)<br/><b>Handle (spell:205984) appropriately in each phase:<br/><b>In Phase 1, run to an isolated area for (spell:206577), then stand on a clump of players to remove (spell:206585)<br/><b>In Phase 2, run to an area dense with (spell:206398) so that (spell:206433) consumes the puddles<br/><b>In Phase 3, run outside the central blue circle to spawn the (npc:104880), and tank it there to avoid (spell:207714)<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation or cooldowns for applications of (spell:206921) and at high stacks of (spell:206388)<br/><b>Use cooldowns for (spell:206577) and (spell:206433) as necessary<br/><b>During Phase 3, when no (npc:104880) is active, tanks should swap around 6 stacks of (spell:214486)<br/><b>The (npc:103758) tank should use cooldowns against high stacks of (spell:214486) damage while the (npc:104880) is alive<br/><b>Use AoE CC or stun abilities when there are several (npc:104688)s nearby| 
|BOSSID|104528| |LVL|110| |NAME|High Botanist Tel'arn| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This encounter is a three-phase fight involving priority target switching, controlled DPS on certain adds, and moderate to heavy movement. As the fight progresses, the boss will summon a second and third 'clone' of itself. These clones are health-linked, so players should use multi-DoT and cleave mechanics to the raid's advantage. Save (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) for the final phase of the fight, as it is the hardest.<br/><br/>Phase 1: The High Botanist<br/><br/><b>(npc:104528) begins the encounter with access to one Arcane ability ((spell:218438)), one Nature ability ((spell:218304)), and one Fire ability ((spell:218155)). <br/><b>Early in the encounter, and about every 35 seconds thereafter, (npc:104528) will cast (spell:218155) at a random player's position.<br/><b>Players struck by the first 1-2 waves of the (spell:218155) will likely survive. Beyond that, the flares are so close together that players are likely to be hit by more than one detonation at once, and instantly die.<br/><b>As soon as the (spell:218155) spawns, all players inside its area should run out between two of the flares. Use a movement-speed boost if you are closer to the middle than the edge, and use a defensive cooldown if you are unlikely to make it out in time.<br/><b>(npc:104528) will target a player with (spell:218304) once every 45-50 seconds.<br/><b>When (spell:218304) goes out, nearby players should move away in case the Lasher it spawns will target them with (spell:218342).<br/><b>(spell:218438) is cast every 35 seconds throughout the phase, targeting a random player's location.<br/><b>In addition, (npc:104528) is empowered with (spell:218502) for the entire encounter.<br/><b>When (npc:104528) reaches 75% health, he will conjure an image of himself named (npc:109038), and funnel his Fire powers into this image. This begins Phase 2 of the encounter.<br/><br/>Phase 2:  Nightosis<br/><br/><b>(npc:104528) retains (spell:218502), (spell:218438), and (spell:218304).<br/><b>(npc:109038) gains the (spell:218155) ability from Phase 1, and also gains (spell:218774).<br/><b>The raid must stagger the Plasma Sphere deaths to avoid excessive (spell:218780) damage.<br/><b>(npc:109038) will cast (spell:218774) every 55 seconds during this phase.<br/><b>(npc:109038) also has a tank attack, (spell:218806), which he will cast about every 8 seconds. This deals light to moderate damage to the tank and all other players within 4 yards. The two tanks should not stack, and other players should make sure to stay away from the (npc:109038) tank's position.<br/><b>When the two Tel'arns reach 50% health, (npc:104528) will conjure an image of himself named (npc:109041), and funnel his Nature powers into this image. This leaves (npc:104528) with only Arcane abilities, and he will become (npc:109040). This begins Phase 3 of the encounter.<br/><br/>Phase 3: Pure Forms<br/><br/><b>In this phase, each of the three bosses will cast spells of a single element.<br/><b>(npc:109038) retains the three abilities he gained in Phase 2, but will use (spell:218774) less frequently, every 70 seconds.<br/><b>(npc:109040) (the Tel'arn formerly known as (npc:104528)) retains (spell:218502) and (spell:218438), and also gains the (spell:218809) mechanic.<br/><b>When (spell:218809) goes out, players who are not targeted should look around for nearby (spell:218809) targets and stand on them.<br/><b>(npc:109041) retains the (spell:218304) ability from the original (npc:104528), and also gains two new abilities: (spell:219009) and (spell:219235).<br/><b>(npc:109041) will cast (spell:219009) every 70 seconds, forming a green pool under one of the three boss's feet.<br/><b>(npc:109041) will cast (spell:219235) frequently.<br/><b>During this phase, tanks should hold the three bosses together, but stand more than 4 yards apart from each other to avoid (spell:218806) damage.<br/><b>Use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) during this phase to shorten it, as it is the most complicated and dangerous of the three phases.| |DPS|<b>Ranged DPS should stay spread out for the whole fight<br/><b>Freely cleave and multi-DoT the bosses since their health pools are shared<br/><b>When Parasitic Lashers spawn, stun or snare them, and kill them quickly<br/><b>Kill the Plasma Sphere that spawns near the bosses quickly, and kill the second Plasma Sphere just as the first Sphere's (spell:218780) debuff fades<br/><b>Always let one Plasma Sphere detonate on its own - do not waste damage on it<br/><b>Move out of (spell:218438) and (spell:218155) areas<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:218809), pair up with an unaffected ally and stick together until the debuff wears off<br/><b>If not affected by (spell:218809), check to see if any nearby players have the debuff, and pair up with them<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:219235), move away from the Spores when they spawn| |HEAL|<b>This fight requires heavy tank healing; spec into strong single-target healing when possible<br/><b>Tanks with high stacks of (spell:218502) will need a lot of healer attention<br/><b>Use minor CDs to recover from (spell:218438)'s raid damage<br/><b>Use major CDs to recover from (spell:218780)'s raid damage<br/><b>Dispel (spell:218304), but check that no other players are standing too close before doing so<br/><b>Players with the (spell:218304) or (spell:219235) debuff will require additional healing<br/><b>Move out of (spell:218438) and (spell:218155) areas<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:218809), pair up with an unaffected ally and stick together until the debuff wears off<br/><b>If not affected by (spell:218809), check to see if any nearby players have the debuff, and pair up with them<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:219235), move away from the Spores when they spawn| |TANK|<b>Taunt-swap (npc:104528)/(npc:109040) at 7 stacks of (spell:218502)<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation and cooldowns while tanking with high stacks of (spell:218502)<br/><b>Move the boss(es) away from nearby (spell:218438) or (spell:218155) areas<br/><b>Once (npc:109038) spawns, tanks should avoid being within 4 yards of one another to limit (spell:218806) damage<br/><b>For the rest of the fight, tank the bosses near one of the Plasma Sphere spawn locations<br/><b>During the final phase, keep the bosses close together<br/><b>Use heavier cooldowns if tanking (npc:109040) and (npc:109041) at the same time<br/><b>Begin moving the bosses away as soon as the (spell:219009) cast begins<br/><b>Move away from (spell:219235)| 
|BOSSID|101002| |LVL|110| |NAME|Krosus| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This encounter is a single-phase fight with a hard "enrage" at 6 minutes, as (npc:101002) will destroy a quarter of the bridge players are fighting him on every 90 seconds. Most of the fight is single-target, but every 90 seconds (npc:101002) will summon a small number of adds that must be killed.<br/><br/>Note that players can walk right off the front of the bridge during the fight. These players will die, and you may struggle to reach them with battle resurrection effects. Take care in positioning, especially with (spell:100)-like effects.<br/><br/>(npc:101002) will cast (spell:205875) every 30 seconds, raising his fists high into the air and then smashing them with great force into the bridge.<br/><br/>(npc:101002) strikes the bridge with such force that the structure will begin to deteriorate. The second (spell:205875) will cause the front quarter of the bridge to fracture, and the third (spell:205875) will destroy the fractured area.<br/><br/>This creates a 6-minute hard "enrage". The raid must defeat (npc:101002) before the 12th (spell:205875) cast.<br/><br/>It is not possible for tanks to soak the third (spell:205875), as to do so would require them to stand on the bridge segment that is being destroyed, and they would fall into the ocean and die. Fortunately, every third (spell:205875) will deal damage to the raid as if it is being soaked, even when it is not.<br/><br/>Once per bridge segment - between the first and second (spell:205875)s on that segment - (npc:101002) will hurl globs of (spell:205420) at the bridge.<br/><br/>On Normal difficulty, he will throw fewer globs of (spell:205420) than there are players in the raid, making it technically possible to soak all (spell:205420)es.<br/><br/>Melee DPS should soak pools nearer to the boss, while ranged DPS and healers should soak the pools that spawn further from the boss. Abilities like (spell:77761) or (spell:192077) are useful for helping the raid reach and soak all the (spell:205420) patches.<br/><br/>If any pools must go unsoaked, they should be ones that are closer to the boss, so that the resulting adds will be easier to kill while maintaining damage on (npc:101002).<br/><br/>(npc:104262) adds have low health and will chain-cast (spell:209017) on random targets.<br/><br/>(npc:101002) will occasionally target a ranged player for (spell:205348), marking that player with a green arrow over their head.<br/><br/>As (npc:101002) destroys the bridge, the maximum distance that players can create by running to the back of the bridge will decrease. This will lead to increased raid damage from (spell:205348) during the later stages of the fight.<br/><br/>This spell is used erratically; the first one occurs early in the fight, and there can be a gap of up to a minute before the next (spell:205348) is cast. Later in the encounter, (npc:101002) may cast (spell:205348) as frequently as every 15 seconds. Players must remain alert and ready to run if targeted, and healers should use cooldowns to recover from more frequent (spell:205348) barrages.<br/><br/>Frequently, (npc:101002) will attack the raid with (spell:205391). This ability is not on a strict timer; it happens erratically throughout the fight.<br/><br/>Dodging the (spell:205391) can be more difficult for players who are running out with (spell:205348) or who are attacking (npc:104262)s. Always orient your camera so you can see (npc:101002).<br/><br/>(spell:206677) is the tank-swap mechanic in the encounter. (npc:101002) will frequently apply (spell:206677) to his primary target.<br/><br/>If at any time (npc:101002) does not have a melee target, he will begin to cast (spell:208203), dealing frequent raid-wide damage.<br/><br/>Otherwise, leave one tank in melee range of (npc:101002) at all times. This means only the off-tank should consider assisting with (spell:205420) soaking duties.| |DPS|<b>Optimize your spec for single-target DPS, as the fight has a hard "enrage"<br/><b>Melee DPS must be sure to move out of the (spell:205875) circles<br/><b>Move to the safe side of the bridge during (spell:205391)<br/><b>Melee DPS should soak nearby (spell:205420)es, while ranged DPS should soak distant ones<br/><b>Interrupt, stun, and quickly kill any (npc:104262) adds that spawn from unsoaked (spell:205420)es<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:205348), use speed boosts to get to the back of the bridge<br/><b>When (npc:101002) begins casting the 3rd (spell:205875) on each bridge segment, run back to the safe portion of the bridge| |HEAL|<b>Tanks will need to be topped off when soaking (spell:205875)<br/><b>The raid will take heavy damage from (spell:205875), (spell:205348), and (spell:205420)<br/><b>Use cooldowns to recover from any heavy-damage (spell:205875) or (spell:205348) events, especially when the raid has less room to work with<br/><b>Move to the safe side of the bridge during (spell:205391)<br/><b>Soak distant (spell:205420)es to prevent (npc:104262)s from spawning<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:205348), use speed boosts to get to the back of the bridge<br/><b>When (npc:101002) begins casting the 3rd (spell:205875) on each bridge segment, run back to the safe portion of the bridge| |TANK|<b>Swap tanking duties on 5-7 stacks of (spell:206677)<br/><b>One tank should stand in each (spell:205875) circle to reduce raid damage<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation/cooldowns to reduce (spell:205875) damage<br/><b>Do not soak the 3rd (spell:205875) on each bridge segment - run to the safe area so you are not killed when the bridge falls away<br/><b>Be sure to leave one tank in melee range of (npc:101002) at all times to avoid (spell:208203) - except during every 3rd (spell:205875), of course<br/><b>Move to the safe side of the bridge during (spell:205391)<br/><b>The off-tank can help soak (spell:205420)<br/><b>Attack and stun/interrupt any (npc:104262)s in range| 
|BOSSID|103685| |LVL|110| |NAME|Tichondrius| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This encounter cycles between two phases in a fixed pattern: Phase 1 lasts for 1:30, then Phase 2 for 30 seconds; this repeats; and then the fight enters Phase 1 for the rest of the encounter.<br/><br/>The first phase is primarily single-target, although (npc:103685) will summon a small number of adds 4 times during the phase, and AoE stuns are useful. The second phase is an adds phase, where players defeat the adds to gain powerful buffs they can apply to (npc:103685) when Phase 1 returns. Each subsequent Phase 1 becomes more difficult as an additional type of add will be summoned.<br/><br/>(spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) should be saved for the final Phase 1, as its extra adds are the most dangerous.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Lord of the Nazrethim<br/><br/><b>Phase 1 has a very rigid structure:<br/><br/>1. (spell:212997)<br/>2. (spell:208230)<br/>3. (spell:213238)<br/>4. Repeat steps 1-3<br/>5. (spell:213531)<br/>6. Repeat steps 1-5<br/>7. Phase 2 begins<br/><br/><b>When each new Phase 1 begins, the events will unfold in this same order.<br/><b>(spell:212997) and (spell:213238) are two linked abilities that, if handled poorly, will result in spreading too many debuffs to the raid and creating unhealable damage.<br/><b>It is important to avoid spreading the (spell:212997) to additional players through the (spell:213238) mechanic. The best way to avoid this is to mark a rough location for players with (spell:212997) to stand.<br/><b>Healers should drop ground-based AoE effects on the (spell:212997) players, and those players should make an effort to stand in the healing AoE without stacking.<br/><b>In between the (spell:212997) and (spell:213238) casts, (npc:103685) will debuff his current tank with (spell:208230).<br/><b>(npc:103685) is buffed with a passive (spell:206893) that causes all of his allies to heal themselves whenever they deal melee damage.<br/><b>All ranged dps should switch to the (npc:108934)s and kill them off quickly. It is important that the (npc:108934)s die before the next (spell:208230) comes in. <br/><b>Twice in each phase, (npc:103685) will channel (spell:213531). This has a 2-second cast time, and an 8-second channel.<br/><b>While hiding behind a (npc:108625) protects the player from damage, each (spell:213531) bolt will damage the (npc:108625) itself! If too many players hide behind the same (npc:108625), it will be destroyed, and those players will begin taking dangerous (spell:213531) damage.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Shadow of Terror<br/><br/><b>(spell:206365) is cast immediately after the second (spell:213531) in each Phase 1. (npc:103685) will pull the raid into a nightmare-shrouded version of the Captain's Quarters.<br/><b>Players should react quickly and move out of the (spell:215988) telegraph to avoid taking its damage.<br/><b>(npc:104326) bats will spawn throughout this phase, at an increasing rate.<br/><b>(spell:206365) lasts for 30 seconds. At the end of the 30 seconds, players will return to reality, and all (npc:104326)s and (spell:206466) orbs will immediately despawn.<br/><b>Note that any adds that were still alive before the (spell:206365) begins will still be alive when the (spell:206365) ends. These adds do not join the raid inside the (spell:206365).<br/><br/>The Nightborne and the Legion<br/><br/><b>Following the first (spell:206365) phase, (npc:103685) will begin to summon allies during each Phase 1 repeat. These adds enter the room from the two doorways in the back, and will rush forward toward (npc:103685), potentially attacking and killing healers if the tank is not ready to pick them up.<br/><b>The second time players enter Phase 1, (npc:103685) will summon (npc:108591)s. Two Spellguards will join the fight every 25-30 seconds<br/><b>(spell:216027)s deal very heavy damage to players standing inside them, and persist for 90 seconds.<br/><b>During the third Phase 1, (npc:103685) will also summon a (npc:108593) each time he summons (npc:108591)s.<br/><b>To avoid the (spell:216040) splash damage, healers should move to the back of the raid when this phase begins, and spread out away from other players. This should allow each healer to instantly dispel themselves when they are afflicted with (spell:216040).<br/><b>The raid should save (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) for this final phase, to deal with these adds quickly and ideally prevent too many of them from spawning.<br/><b>Note that both of these types of adds can be affected by (spell:206893), and must be kept more than 30 yards from (npc:103685). Whichever tank is not actively tanking should pick these adds up and tank them in the (spell:208230)/(npc:108934) tanking location.| |DPS|<b>Be attentive to (spell:212997); if you get it, run to the designated (spell:212997) area<br/><b>Otherwise, do not stand in the (spell:212997) area at all, so you are not struck by (spell:213238)<br/><b>When (npc:108934) spawns, use AoE stuns and burst AoE damage to quickly kill them<br/><b>Hide behind a (npc:108625) during (spell:213531)<br/><b>During Phase 2, kill as many (npc:104326)s as possible<br/><b>Step out of (spell:215988) areas<br/><b>Take an (spell:206466) buff when available<br/><b>Prioritize killing (npc:108593)s and (npc:108591)s during subsequent Phase 1 phases<br/><b>Move away from the raid as (spell:216024) is about to expire, so your (spell:216027) is out of the way| |HEAL|<b>Tank healing will be heavy during (spell:208230)/(npc:108934)<br/><b>Raid healing will be heavier when more players are affected by (spell:212997), at the end of the phase<br/><b>Use cooldowns at the start of (spell:213531) while the raid gets into position<br/><b>Use extra cooldowns during (spell:206365) to heal through lingering (spell:212997) and (spell:215988) damage<br/><b>Be attentive to (spell:212997); if you get it, run to the designated (spell:212997) area<br/><b>Otherwise, do not stand in the (spell:212997) area at all, so you are not struck by (spell:213238)<br/><b>Hide behind a (npc:108625) during (spell:213531)<br/><b>Step out of (spell:215988) areas<br/><b>Take an (spell:206466) buff when available<br/><b>During subsequent Phase 1 phases, move away from the raid as (spell:216024) is about to expire, so your (spell:216027) is out of the way<br/><b>During the final Phase 1, stay spread out so you can instantly dispel (spell:216040) from yourself| |TANK|<b>Tank (npc:103685) where he stands<br/><b>Taunt swap on each (spell:208230) debuff<br/><b>The (spell:208230) tank should run away to the marked location so (npc:108934)s do not heal<br/><b>Use Active Mitigation or cooldowns to withstand the (npc:108934)s' melee damage<br/><b>Hide behind a (npc:108625) during (spell:213531)<br/><b>Never stand in between the boss and players with (spell:212997)<br/><b>During Phase 2, group up the (npc:104326)s so they can be easily killed<br/><b>Step out of (spell:215988) areas<br/><b>Only take an (spell:206466) buff once all the priority players have one<br/><b>The off-tank should pick up the (npc:108591)s and (npc:108593) adds that come from the back of the room in subsequent Phase 1 phases| 
|BOSSID|110965| |LVL|110| |NAME|Elisande| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This encounter features heavy movement and frequent high-priority target swaps. The fight has a three-phase structure, and (npc:110965) uses more complex abilities in later phases.<br/><br/>(npc:110965) will begin the encounter by casting (spell:208865), dealing damage to nearby players as she lands. <br/><br/>Players must bring (npc:110965) to 10% health to initiate a new phase. When this happens, (npc:110965) will cast (spell:208944) and disappear into the Nightwell, healing to full health. After 10 seconds, she will (spell:208865) and begin the next phase.<br/><br/>Each phase gets progressively harder because, when (npc:110965) uses certain abilities ((spell:233066) on Normal and (spell:228877), (spell:210024) on Heroic), she leaves behind an (npc:105622) at her position that will cast those abilities again in subsequent phases.<br/><br/>The (npc:110965) encounter can be a long fight. Depending on your raid's performance, it may be possible to get two casts of (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) - one at the start of the encounter, and again during the third and hardest phase. A raid that will get only one cast of (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) will have to decide between using it during Phase 1, to reduce the number of (spell:228877) casts that will be echoed later, or during Phase 3, where the fight is the most difficult.<br/><br/>All Phases<br/><br/><b>At varying intervals throughout the fight, (npc:110965) will summon Time Elementals to assist her. When the Time Elementals die, they will create a "time zone" that distorts the flow of time within its boundaries.<br/><b>Recursive Elementals are blue, do not have to be tanked, and cannot be moved.<br/><b>When a Recursive Elemental dies, it forms a (spell:209165) bubble on its corpse's location.<br/><b>(npc:105301)s are pink, should be tanked, and can be moved.<br/><b>When an (npc:105301) dies, it forms a (spell:209166) zone on its corpse's location.<br/><b>Note that (npc:110965) and other enemies do not benefit from the (spell:209165)/(spell:209166) mechanics themselves.<br/><b>The (spell:209166) zone will last for 30 seconds and the (spell:209165) zone will last for a full minute. All players should try and maintain the (spell:209166) buff on themselves as much as possible, whilst players should generally avoid taking the (spell:209165) zone debuff. Instead, players should try and be near the (spell:209165) zone to help deal with incoming abilities.<br/><br/>Recursive and (npc:105301)s will spawn at the same, or similar, times in each phase. For Normal mode, this looks like:<br/><br/><b>10-15 seconds into the phase, a Recursive Elemental and an (npc:105301) will spawn<br/><b>At about 1:00 into the phase, a Recursive Elemental will spawn<br/><b>At about 1:40 into the phase, an (npc:105301) will spawn<br/><b>At 1:50 into the phase, a Recursive Elemental will spawn<br/><b>At 2:50 into the phase, a Recursive Elementa will spawn<br/><b>At about 3:15 into the phase, an (npc:105301) will spawn<br/><br/><b>When both a Recursive and an (npc:105301) spawn, the Recursive Elemental should be the primary kill target: as you will want access to the (spell:209165) zone to use to dodge certain encounter mechanics.<br/><b>In addition, (npc:110965) will attack targets with (spell:229738) throughout all phases of the fight. This ability deals moderate damage to its target, and then lashes out to additional players. As a phase progresses, (spell:229738) will target fewer additional players, reducing the healing requirements to deal with this mechanic.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Time Layer 1<br/><br/><b>During the first phase, (npc:110965) will use (spell:228877) and (spell:233066). (spell:233066) patches will echo into future phases, so reducing the number (spell:233066) casts that can occur in Phase 1, by using (spell:209166) as a DPS boost and by using (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353), makes subsequent phases less difficult.<br/><b>About 30-40 seconds into the phase, (npc:110965) will teleport to a random location in the room and cast (spell:228877). This will summon a large number of (spell:228877)s at the edges of the room, that will then begin to move toward (npc:110965)'s location.<br/><b>However, (spell:228877) projectiles that pass through (spell:209165) or (spell:209166) will have their movement speed permanently augmented by those zones' effects.<br/><b>Whenever possible, the raid should kill an (npc:105301) next to a (spell:209165) zone to create this arrangement and dodge (spell:228877)s more easily.<br/><b>Periodically, (npc:110965) will target a random player with (spell:233066), creating a large pool of Arcane energy at that player's location. There is no warning graphic for this ability.<br/><b>In future phases, (npc:110965) will not cast (spell:233066) herself, but (spell:233066) pools will appear at the same location and the same relative time as they did in Phase 1. So for example, if the first (spell:233066) was cast at 20 seconds into Phase 1, a (spell:233066) will form in that same location 20 seconds into Phase 2, and again 20 seconds into Phase 3. These (spell:233066) pools should also be soaked up if they interfere with the raid's positioning or strategy.<br/><b>(npc:110965) will attack her tank with (spell:209615), a stacking DoT effect.<br/><b>When (npc:110965) reaches 10% health remaining, she will cast (spell:208944), freezing players in place for 7 seconds. She will leap into the Nightwell, heal to full health, and then (spell:208865). Players regain control of their characters just before (spell:208865), and can move out of the way to avoid taking its damage.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Time Layer 2<br/><br/><b>During Phase 2, (spell:233066) will occur at the same times, and from the same locations, as they occurred during Phase 1.<br/><b>(npc:110965) also gains the ability to rip holes into reality itself and summon (spell:210024)s.<br/><b>(npc:110965) will summon multiple (spell:210024)s each time she uses this ability. The timing between (spell:210024)s is erratic, with intervals between casts being as short as 20 seconds and as long as 1:10. Players must be ready to react quickly to (spell:210024) spawns.<br/><b>(npc:110965) will begin to use her (spell:214278) ability in this phase, marking several players and then firing Arcane beams at them.<br/><b>As soon as the first (spell:214278)s have been fired, (npc:110965) marks a second set of players and repeats the process.<br/><b>Players marked by (spell:214278) should move close to (npc:110965) to limit the number of players that may be struck.<br/><b>During this phase, (npc:110965) will attack the tanks with (spell:209973), which she casts every 20-25 seconds.<br/><b>When (npc:110965) reaches 10% health remaining, she will cast (spell:208944), freezing players in place for 7 seconds. She will leap into the Nightwell, heal to full health, and then (spell:208865). Players regain control of their characters just before (spell:208865), and can move out of the way to avoid taking its damage.<br/><br/>Phase 3: Time Layer 3<br/><br/><b>During Phase 3, (spell:233066) will continue to occur at the same times, and from the same locations, as they occurred during Phase 1.<br/><b>The two abilities that (npc:110965) will gain for Phase 3, (spell:209598) and (spell:211258), are both debuffs that she places on random players. <br/><b>(spell:209598) is cast approximately every 40 seconds, and will target a larger amount of players with each cast. This debuff deals no damage while applied, but will detonate, dealing heavy damage to the entire raid, when it expires.<br/><br/>As an example, if three players were targeted by (spell:209598):<br/><br/><b>One player with (spell:209598) should duck into the (spell:209165) bubble to delay its detonation<br/><b>One player with (spell:209598) should duck into the (spell:209166) bubble to accelerate its detonation<br/><b>If there is a third (spell:209598) target, that player should not use either debuff, and instead let (spell:209598) expire naturally<br/><br/><b>This strategy will space out the (spell:209598) detonations, allowing healers the chance to top up the raid between each explosion and prevent deaths.<br/><b>(spell:211258) is cast very erratically, and will affect 4 targets with each cast.<br/><b>(spell:211258)'s damage is dangerous in conjunction with (spell:233066), or when (spell:228877)s or (spell:209598)s are dealing raid damage. Healers should make sure to top off the (spell:211258) targets during these effects.<br/><b>(npc:110965) will cast (spell:209971) at her current tank target every 10 seconds.<br/><b>If an (spell:209971) is not interrupted and the targeted tank becomes  Ablated, the tanks should swap (npc:110965)-tanking duties. Continue swapping as necessary to ensure the tank with the least stacks of  Ablated is tanking. However, it is far safer to interrupt every (spell:209971) cast.<br/><b>Most of the challenge of this phase comes from the slow attrition of dealing with (spell:211258) and (spell:209598).<br/><b>If your group did not use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) to shorten Phase 1, or if (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) become available again during this phase, use it to shorten Phase 3, as it is the most difficult phase in the fight.| |DPS|<b>Interrupt the Recursive Elemental's (spell:221864) and the (npc:105301)'s (spell:209568) casts<br/><b>Always prioritize the Elementals over (npc:110965)<br/><b>Soak (spell:233066) pools if you have a defensive cooldown available<br/><b>Dodge (spell:228877)s by running through the gaps created when they pass through the (spell:209165)/(spell:209166) zones<br/><b>Use the (spell:209166) debuff as a DPS boost<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:214278), move close to (npc:110965) and do not stack on other players<br/><b>When (spell:210024)s spawn, look for a nearby impact location and stand in it<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:209598), call out whether you will use the (spell:209165)/(spell:209166) debuff or let it expire naturally<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:211258), avoid gaining the (spell:209166) debuff| |HEAL|<b>(spell:228877)s, unsoaked (spell:210024)s, and (spell:209598) will all deal high raid damage and may require cooldowns<br/><b>Players affected by (spell:233066), (spell:214278), and (spell:211258) debuffs will require additional healing<br/><b>Be sure to top off the tank with (spell:209973) before the debuff detonates<br/><b>Soak (spell:233066) pools if you have a defensive cooldown available<br/><b>Dodge (spell:228877)s by running through the gaps created when they pass through the (spell:209165)/(spell:209166) zones<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:214278), move close to (npc:110965) and do not stack on other players<br/><b>When (spell:210024)s spawn, look for a nearby impact location and stand in it<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:209598), call out whether you will use the (spell:209165)/(spell:209166) debuff or let it expire naturally<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:211258), avoid gaining the (spell:209166) debuff| |TANK|<b>The (npc:105301) must be tanked, and should not be tanked by the (npc:110965) tank<br/><b>Move the enemies so they are close together for cleave damage, and so that (spell:209165)/(spell:209166) zones will spawn adjacent to one another, but not overlapping<br/><br/>During Phase 1:<br/><br/><b>Taunt-swap on 4 stacks of (spell:209615), or after an (npc:105301) dies<br/><b>Pull (npc:110965) away from nearby (spell:233066) pools to protect the melee DPS<br/><b>Dodge the (spell:228877)s through the gap created by the (spell:209165)/(spell:209166) zones<br/><br/>During Phase 2:<br/><br/><b>Taunt-swap when the current tank becomes afflicted with (spell:209973)<br/><b>The (spell:209973) tank should run away as the debuff expires<br/><b>Move (npc:110965) away from nearby (spell:233066) pools<br/><b>Do not move (npc:110965) during (spell:214278), so that players are not surprised by sudden changes in the indicating arrows' direction<br/><br/>During Phase 3:<br/><br/><b>Position (npc:110965) away from her (spell:228877) echoes so players have time to dodge<br/><b>Interrupt (npc:110965)'s (spell:209971) casts, and taunt-swap if she successfully casts it<br/><b>Move (npc:110965) away from nearby (spell:233066) pools| 
|BOSSID|105503| |LVL|110| |NAME|Gul'dan| |MAPID|1088| |ST|This is a three phase encounter which requires the raid to deal three mini-bosses in the first phase, followed by a direct confrontation against (npc:105503) himself in the following two phases. The raid requires a large amount of precise positioning and co-ordination in order to counter the mechanics (npc:105503) throws at you, as well as consistently high dps to beat his 12 minute enrage.<br/><br/>Essence of Aman'Thul<br/><br/><b>Throughout Phase One and Two, players have access to an additional ability by using an extra action button. The ability players gain depends on which role they are playing.<br/><br/><b>Tanks gain (spell:210296): Once used, it will cause that player to absorb all damage taken for 6 seconds.<br/><b>Healers gain (spell:217830): Once used, it will cause that player to create a protective shield around them, absorbing 50% of fire damage taken up to a cap, shared among allies within 10 yards.<br/><b>DPS gain (spell:210339): Once used, it will increase that players casting, movement, and attack speed by 30% as well as decreasing cooldowns by 30% and causing their Periodic Effects to occur 30% faster.<br/><br/><b>If the player receives any fire damage whilst (spell:210339) is active, it will remove the effect. <br/><b>Each of the abilities gained will help players counter mechanics and abilities that (npc:105503) and his mini-bosses challenge the raid with. These points will be covered throughout the guide.<br/><br/>Phase 1: The Council of Elders<br/><br/><b>At the beginning of Phase One, players can attack (npc:105503) until he summons all three of his mini-bosses, at which point he will become immune to damage inside the (spell:206516) in the middle of the room.<br/><b>(npc:105503) does not need to be tanked during this phase, as he is instead chain casting two abilities.<br/><b>(npc:105503) casts (spell:206219). He marks a location of a random ranged player and throws a ball of fire towards it, dealing large raid wide damage which drops off the further away players are from it.<br/><b>(npc:105503) will also cast (spell:206514). He faces a direction and sends out a large beam of fire, dealing a large amount of ticking fire damage to anyone who stands inside it.<br/><b>When (npc:105503) summons his demon mini-bosses, he will do so through the use of (spell:212256).<br/><b>(npc:104537) will spawn first and will cast (spell:206675) on his primary target. This short cast deals an enormous amount of fire damage to the tank and will most likely kill them.<br/><b>(npc:104536) will spawn second. He will frequently teleport around the encounter area by using his (spell:207939) ability.<br/><b>The eyes will remain active throughout phase one.<br/><b>(npc:104534) will spawn third and will cast (spell:206883) on the tank. This spell will hurl a soul cage at his target.<br/><b>To make sure that the encounter area in Phase One remains clean, (npc:104536) must be killed as soon as possible.<br/><b>After the mini-bosses are dead, players should move towards the free area of the room and get close to (npc:105503) as he deals damage and knocks back all players upon entering Phase Two and any player who is knocked off the edge of the platform will fall to their death.<br/><br/>Phase 2: The Ritual of Aman'Thul<br/><br/><b>After knocking back all players, (npc:105503) will become damageable once again.<br/><b>(npc:105503) has 3 new abilities that the raid needs to deal with in this phase. <br/><b>(spell:206222) will place a debuff on multiple members of the raid. The debuff deals ticking fire damage and slows the player by 50%.<br/><b>(npc:105503) will spawn multiple (spell:209270) adds. These eyes will hover near (npc:105503) and channel shadow energy at a random player, dealing a large amount of ever increasing shadow damage to that player and anyone within 8 yards of them.<br/><b>Whenever anyone is within 2 yards of (npc:105503)'s primary target, he will cast (spell:227554) at the primary target.<br/><b>(npc:105503) also has an energy bar. This energy is used up whenever he casts (spell:227554).<br/><b>You want to have (npc:105503) use this ability often enough so that the damage isn't too high from the energy, but not so often that his attack speed buff starts stacking.<br/><b>Throughout the phase (npc:105503) will empower his abilities at certain health breakpoints. <br/><br/><b>At 85% he will empower his (spell:206222). The (spell:206221) will knock the player directly away from (npc:105503) and the bind them to that location. The damage and slow from the ability is also increased.<br/><b>At 70% he will empower his (spell:206219), causing it to deal more damage, as well as leave a patch of fire on the ground for 3 minutes.<br/><b>At 55%, he will empower his (spell:209270).<br/><br/><b>Once (npc:105503) reaches 40% HP, Phase Three will begin.<br/><br/>Phase 3: The Master's Power<br/><br/><b>(npc:105503) will briefly become immune in the middle of the room, and then emerge in an empowered state.<br/><b>Players in this phase must deal with mechanics quickly and efficiently in order to successfully defeat (npc:105503):<br/><br/><b>Tanks want to drag (npc:105503) to one side of the platform. Throughout this phase you will need to continue to deal with his (spell:227554) every 11-12 seconds, just like in phase 2.<br/><b>Ranged players will then want to spread out on one side of the room in smaller raid sizes, or two sides in larger raid sizes.<br/><b>This will help deal with the incoming (spell:211152).<br/><br/><b>The (spell:211152) works the same as it did in phase 2 and it must be killed off as soon as possible, as there is a large amount of raid wide damage present in this phase.<br/><b>Ranged players being spread also helps the raid deal with a new ability which is the (spell:228190).<br/><b>Whilst placing the (spell:228190), you can severely limit the the amount of room the (spell:221781) takes up by controlling your movement.<br/><b>Throughout this phase, (npc:105503) will be placing (spell:221891) debuffs on players.<br/><b>To remove the souls, ranged players need to stand within the well, this will deal a low amount of ticking damage to them every second, and for every 3 seconds a player is within the well, a soul will be removed.<br/><b>When (spell:206744) is cast, it is important that you use a healing cooldown. Players who have other abilities on them during this time, such as the (spell:228190), should use personal damage reduction cooldowns to help survive the heavy incoming damage. <br/><b>Another ability (npc:105503) will cast is (spell:161121). This is a series of four explosions which are blasted out from (npc:105503)'s position.<br/><b>One bad crossover point is after the second (spell:161121) is cast. Before teleporting to the tank, he will summon an (spell:211152).| |DPS|Phase 1<br/><br/><b>Avoid standing within (npc:105503)'s (spell:206514) and (spell:212256).<br/><b>Ranged players should stack up whilst healers use (spell:217830) to mitigate the damage of (spell:206219).<br/><b>Stick to one side of the room whilst (npc:104536) is active. This will keep the other side of the room clear of his (npc:106986) eye beams.<br/><b>Save cooldowns and (spell:210339) for when (npc:104536) spawns. This will reduce the amount of (npc:106986) eye beams in the encounter area.<br/><br/>Phase 2<br/><br/><b>Ranged players should stack 10 yards behind the (npc:105503) so that the ranged (spell:206222) targets can move to break their bonds into melee. Whilst the melee (spell:206222) targets break into ranged.<br/><b>(spell:209270) should be swapped to and killed off as soon as possible, preferably with players using (spell:210339). Players targeted by their beams should move 8 yards away from any other player.<br/><b>Players should run over to targets affected by the (spell:206221) so that they can break their bonds without taking lethal damage, whilst the tank breaks their bonds solo by 