097) mechanic.<br/><b>After the second (spell:202977) cast, (npc:102672) is out of Energy and will collapse, starting the (spell:203552) phase.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Heart of the Swarm<br/><br/><b>During the (spell:203552) phase, (npc:102672) will draw all existing patches of (spell:203537) toward her position, absorbing them. The (spell:203537) will still inflict damage to players it passes through as it moves toward her.<br/><b>While this is happening, the floor of the room becomes littered with small insects. Every few seconds, a handful of insects will begin to grow, forming (npc:102998).<br/><b>(spell:203552) lasts for 20 seconds. At the end of the phase, (npc:102672) will have 100 Energy, and will stand up, resuming the Plagued Dreamer phase.<br/><br/>Note that after each (spell:203552) phase, (npc:102672) will target one additional player with (spell:203097) each time she casts it.<br/><br/>Berserk<br/><br/><b>(npc:102672) has a 10-minute (spell:47008) timer on Normal difficulty, which occurs at the end of her 5th (spell:203552) phase.| |DPS|<b>Use your most powerful cooldowns at the start of the fight with (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353)<br/><b>If affected by (spell:203097), move to the nearest wall to drop your (spell:203537)<br/><b>When (npc:102672) casts (spell:202977), use movement-speed abilities to get out of the area of effect<br/><b>Use a damage-reduction cooldown if you will take multiple ticks of (spell:202977) while running through it<br/><b>During (spell:203552), deal as much damage as you can to (npc:102672) while dodging (spell:203646) damage| |HEAL|<b>Be sure to keep (spell:203097) targets topped up, and heal the tanks<br/><b>Use HoTs and instant spells to heal players who take (spell:202977) damage<br/><b>Use AoE healing to recover from the raidwide (spell:204463) explosion<br/><b>Tanks will take heavy damage from their (spell:204463) explosion<br/><b>The third (spell:204463) is the most dangerous, as (npc:102672) is casting (spell:202977) at the same time, and players who take (spell:202977) damage may dip quite low<br/><b>If affected by  Rot, move to the nearest wall to drop your (spell:203537)<br/><b>When (npc:102672) casts (spell:202977), use movement-speed abilities to get out of the area of effect<br/><b>Use a damage-reduction cooldown if you will take multiple ticks of (spell:202977) while running through it<br/><b>During (spell:203552), dodge (spell:203646) damage and heal players who take damage from it<br/><b>If your raid performs this phase well, you should be able to recover mana and contribute DPS| |TANK|<b>Taunt (npc:102672) when your co-tank receives the (spell:204463) debuff<br/><b>When you receive the (spell:204463) debuff, run out to a designated area<br/><b>Use a cooldown as the debuff expires to mitigate the (spell:204463) detonation damage<br/><b>After (npc:102672) casts the first (spell:202977) of a phase, drag her back into a fresh quadrant of the room<br/><b>During (spell:203552), deal as much damage as you can to (npc:102672) while dodging (spell:203646) damage| 
|BOSSID|106087| |LVL|110| |NAME|Elerethe Renferal| |MAPID|1094| |ST|This encounter is a complicated two-phase fight with heavy movement requirements and an emphasis on raid awareness.<br/><br/>(npc:106087) will take on two forms during the fight: Spider form and Roc form. Each form has a unique set of abilities that players must master.<br/><br/>Throughout the fight, players must avoid stepping on the (npc:112078)s that line the edges of the platforms.<br/><br/>If players do step on a (npc:112078), tanks should take care to pick up the Skittering Spiderlings, and healers should quickly top up the players struck by (spell:215503).<br/><br/>In addition, stepping on the web bridges that stretch between the platforms can spawn a (npc:111933).<br/><br/>Since the duration of Spider and Roc forms is timed, the raid should use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) at the start of the fight where there is less movement and fewer mechanics to deal with.<br/><br/>If at any time (npc:106087) steps on one of the web bridges leading to another platform, she will gain the (spell:222063) buff. This buff will persist for the remainder of the encounter. Avoid this by making sure never to bring (npc:106087) near a web bridge!<br/><br/>Phase 1: Spider Form<br/><br/><b>Each Spider form phase lasts 90 seconds, with an additional 8-second "intermission" as (npc:106087) becomes briefly unable to attack while transforming into Roc form.<br/><b>Shortly after the fight begins, (npc:106087) casts (spell:215300), linking two pairs of players together.<br/><b>Note that damage that is absorbed does not get transferred through (spell:215300).<br/><b>(npc:106087) will frequently target random players with (spell:218831), a dangerous debuff that must be handled quickly to reduce raid damage<br/><b>Healers should focus these players with additional healing, as they will likely take a few ticks of (spell:223065) damage on top of the heavy (spell:218831) DoT.<br/><b>Twice during each Spider phase, (npc:106087) will retreat to the web above players' heads, and summon a handful of (npc:111933)s.<br/><b>The raid should make sure to kill the (npc:111933)s quickly, but wait for the off-tank to pull them away from (npc:106087) so the (spell:223065)s their corpses spawn will be out of the way.<br/><b>(spell:214348)es occur 50 seconds apart. Shortly after the second (spell:214348), (npc:106087) will reach 100 Energy and begin to transition to Roc form.<br/><br/>Phase 2: Roc Form<br/><br/><b>The Roc form phase lasts 2 minutes, with an 8 second lag at the start and end while (npc:106087) changes forms. Each Roc phase also includes an "interlude" where players must chase (npc:106087) to a new platform. Players should save their strongest defensive or healing cooldowns for this "interlude" portion of the fight, as it is the most dangerous.<br/><b>Shortly after transforming into Roc form, still on the original platform, (npc:106087) will target two players with (spell:210863).<br/><b>The players targeted by (spell:210863) on this first platform should be sure to drop their tornadoes away from the path to the next platform.<br/><b>(npc:106087) will then begin to cast (spell:212707), drawing in power so she can take flight.<br/><b>After (spell:212707) completes, (npc:106087) will take off and fly to the next platform.<br/><b>When (npc:106087) takes off, 9 (spell:212993)s drop from her wings.<br/><b>The (spell:212993) buff lasts for 25 seconds, so these players can jump multiple times if necessary. (Note that jumping while in the air does not work - this isn't a flying mechanic.)<br/><b>The raid members who do not take the (spell:212993)s must cross the web bridge to (npc:106087)'s platform.<br/><b>By the time the raid reaches (npc:106087)'s new platform, most players' health will be quite low. The healing team should use a powerful cooldown to quickly recover from the combination of (spell:212707)/(spell:210948)/(npc:111933) melee damage.<br/><b>When the raid reaches the second platform, (npc:106087) will resume using (spell:210863), casting it three more times during the phase. Targeted players should drop the (spell:210863) in the area behind the raid, and tanks should drag (npc:106087) away as the tornadoes begin to fill the area.<br/><b>(npc:106087) will also begin viciously attacking the tanks with (spell:215582).<br/><b>Immediately after the second (spell:215582) strike, (npc:106087) will cast (spell:210547).<br/><b>When (npc:106087) reaches 100 Energy, she will shift back into her Spider form. Since spiders cannot fly, she will not move to a new platform. If the raid has dealt with (spell:210863) properly, there should still be plenty of room on the large 2nd platform to handle the (spell:218831) and (spell:214348) mechanics.| |DPS|Wait until (npc:111933)s are pulled away from the raid before switching to them<br/><br/>During Spider form:<br/><br/><b>If you are targeted with (spell:215300), move closer to the player you are linked to<br/><b>If affected by (spell:218831), move away from the raid during the initial 10-second debuff<br/><b>During the subsequent 5-second (spell:218831) debuff, keep moving to drop a trail of (spell:223065)s at the edge of the room<br/><b>Run to the opposite side of the platform for (spell:214348)<br/><b>If assigned to take a (spell:212993), use the Extra Action Button to eliminate (npc:111933)s once the tank gathers them<br/><b>If not assigned to take a (spell:212993), run across the webs to the second platform, avoiding (npc:112078)s and (spell:210863) tornadoes<br/><br/>During Roc form:<br/><br/><b>If affected by the (spell:210863) debuff, pop a defensive cooldown and run over (spell:223065)s to clear them<br/><b>Spawn the (spell:210863) tornado in a safe location<br/><b>If possible, put your back to a wall during (spell:212707)<br/><b>Do not be in front of (npc:106087) during (spell:210547)| |HEAL|Tanks will take heavy damage during (spell:215300), (spell:210547), and (spell:215582)<br/>Use raid c