|BOSSID|105393| |LVL|110| |NAME|Il'gynoth| |MAPID|1094| |ST|This encounter is a two-phase fight with heavy movement and awareness requirements. The first phase is multi-target and hectic; players must attack lesser adds that the boss summons to protect herself. The second phase is a single-target, 50-second "burn phase" on (npc:105393)'s true form. <br/><br/>Players must defeat (npc:105393) within two of these "burn phases" or else (npc:105393) grows bored and slaughters the raid with (spell:223121).<br/><br/>Phase 1: The Ruined Ground<br/><br/><b>The aim of Phase 1 is to defeat the (npc:105906), which is preventing players from accessing the vulnerable heart of (npc:105393).<br/><br/><b>The (npc:105906) is buffed by (spell:209915), and takes 99% reduced damage from players<br/><b>To kill the (npc:105906), players must defeat the adds that spawn gradually around the encounter area<br/><b>Killing these adds will spawn (npc:105721), small slimes that will (spell:210099) on random targets<br/><b>If a (npc:105721) is killed near the (npc:105906), its (spell:209471) will deal damage directly to the Eye<br/><br/><b>The raid must kill 20 (npc:105721) adds in range of the (npc:105906) to gain access to (npc:105393) and enter Phase 2.<br/><b>The fight has a rhythmic flow of killing the large adds, then using downtime between add spawns to kite (npc:105721)s to the (npc:105906) and blowing them up to damage the Eye. Adds will continue to spawn for as long as the (npc:105906) is alive, so if players miss with some of the (npc:105721)s' (spell:209471)s, the fight is still recoverable.<br/><b>There are four types of adds that players will be faced with during the fight. Killing each type of add generates a different amount of (npc:105721) spawns.<br/><br/><b>(npc:105304)s spawn 4 (npc:105721) upon dying<br/><b>(npc:105322)s spawn 2 (npc:105721) upon dying<br/><b>(npc:105591)s spawn 4 (npc:105721) upon dying<br/><b>(npc:105383)s spawn 1 (npc:105721) upon dying<br/><br/><b>The encounter begins with the (npc:105906) flanked with two (npc:105304)s.<br/><b>The raid should assign at least one melee DPS to each (npc:105304), so that the tentacles have a melee DPS target for (spell:208689). If (spell:208689) targets a ranged DPS, it may be very difficult for the ranged DPS to get the (spell:208689) away from the raid quickly enough, and the raid may take excess damage.<br/><b>Shortly into the fight, (npc:105393) will spawn a (npc:105322) to attack the raid.<br/><b>Approximately one minute into the encounter, the (npc:105906) will scorch the ground with a fiery beam, summoning a (npc:105591) in the center of the room.<br/><b>The (npc:105591) has very high health and is a low-priority kill target. Tanks should drag the Horror over to the other tentacles that spawn, keeping them within cleave/AoE range, but trying to avoid dropping (spell:212886) on melee DPS.<br/><b>The final type of add spawn players will face in the encounter is the (npc:105383).<br/><b>No player should ever bring their (spell:208929) debuff into the (npc:105906) where (npc:105721)s are being killed. The (spell:212886) patches will make it difficult for players kiting or attacking the Ichors to deal damage or heal, and will deal excess extremely heavy damage to players performing these roles.<br/><br/>The kill order should generally be:<br/><br/>1.(npc:105721)s that are in place to damage the (npc:105906)2.(npc:105383)s3.(npc:105322)s4.(npc:105304)s5.(npc:105591)<br/><br/><b>However, be sure to assign a couple of players to watch the (npc:105322)s and interrupt (spell:208697) even if (npc:105383)s are active.<br/><b>The (npc:105906) will also defend (npc:105393) by attacking players with (spell:210931).<br/><br/><br/><b>Once the (npc:105906) is dead, (npc:105393) will stop spawning new adds, and Phase 2 begins.<br/><br/>Phase 2: The Heart of Corruption<br/><br/><b>The objective of this phase is to kill (npc:105393), the heart-shaped mass at the center of the tree. The encounter is completed only when players bring (npc:105393) to 0 health.<br/><b>As soon as the (npc:105906) dies, (npc:105393) will begin casting (spell:210781).<br/><b>Because of the movement involved in entering and exiting the heart chamber, players are likely to have just over 40 seconds of DPS uptime on the boss.<br/><b>Every fifteen seconds - three times during the phase - (npc:105393) will afflict random raid members with (spell:215128).<br/><b>The raid can use the third (spell:215128) detonation as a benchmark for when to exit the heart chamber.<br/><b>It is possible to defeat (npc:105393) during the first Heart of Corruption phase, but at the intended gear level it is unlikely that the average group will do so.<br/><b>If players fail to kill (npc:105393) during their first Phase 2 attempt, they must exit the heart chamber and repeat Phase 1, killing 20 (npc:105721)s to defeat the respawned (npc:105906). This repeat of Phase 1 spawns adds in a different order.<br/><b>Upon defeating the second (npc:105906), the raid will be allowed to enter the heart chamber again. (npc:105393) will now be channeling (spell:223121), a 90-second cast that instantly wipes the raid if it completes, so the raid must defeat (npc:105393) during this phase. Ideally (npc:105393) should be below 40% health when players finish the first Phase 2, so that he can be killed without (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) in the second Phase 2.| |DPS|<br/>The (npc:105906) takes 99% reduced damage, so players should not waste resources DPSing it directly<br/><b>Prioritize (npc:105721)s in position > (npc:105383)s > (npc:105322)s > (npc:105304)s > (npc:105591)<br/><b>When targeted by a (npc:105721)'s (spell:210099), kite the Ichor to the (npc:105906)<br/><b>Use AoE stuns and slows on the Ichors to prevent taking stacks of (spell:209469)<br/><b>Only kill (npc:105721)s when they are close to the (npc:105906)<br/><b>Interrupt the (npc:105322)s' (spell:208697) when possible<br/><b>If affected by (spell:208929), drop (spell:212886) pools away from the (npc:105906)<br/><b>Dodge the (npc:105304)s' (spell:208689)<br/><b>Save long, major cooldowns for the first Heart of Corruption phase (3 minute cooldowns should be back if used on pull)<br/><b>Deal as much damage to (npc:105393) as possible<br/><b>Move away from other players if debuffed with (spell:215128), and use a personal defensive cooldown to survive the damage<br/><b>Exit the heart chamber before (spell:210781) completes| |HEAL|<br/>Tanks will take heavy damage while tanking (npc:105304)s or the (npc:105591)<br/><b>Use external cooldowns on tanks for the third (spell:210984) they take in a row<br/><b>Dispel (spell:209469) from players who are on low health<br/><b>Focus extra healing on players targeted by (spell:208697) or (spell:208929)<br/><b>When targeted by a (npc:105721)'s (spell:210099), kite the Ichor to the (npc:105906)<br/><b>If affected by (spell:208929), drop (spell:212886) pools away from the (npc:105906)<br/><b>Dodge the (npc:105304)s' (spell:208689)<br/><b>During the Heart of Corruption phase, deal as much damage to (npc:105393) as possible<br/><b>Keep the (spell:215128) targets on high health so the (spell:215128) detonation does not kill them<br/><b>Move away from other players if debuffed with (spell:215128), and use a personal defensive cooldown to survive the damage<br/><b>Exit the heart chamber before (spell:210781) completes<br/><b>Use cooldowns to recover from the second or third sets of (spell:215128) debuffs, or whenever the raid is low during phase 1| |TANK|<br/>Tank the (npc:105304)s and use Active Mitigation or cooldowns against (spell:215234)<br/><b>Dodge the (npc:105304)s' (spell:208689) when possible<br/><b>Pick up the (npc:105591) when it spawns, and swap on 3 stacks of (spell:210984)<br/><b>Use more powerful cooldowns against the second and third (spell:210984)<br/><b>Position the (npc:105591) carefully to avoid dropping (spell:212886) on melee DPS<br/><b>When neither (npc:105591)s or (npc:105304)s are active, DPS the top kill priority target<br/><b>Interrupt the (npc:105322)s' (spell:208697) when possible<br/><b>During the Heart of Corruption phase, deal as much damage as possible to (npc:105393)<br/><b>Move away from other players if debuffed with (spell:215128)<br/><b>Exit the heart chamber before (spell:210781) completes| 
|BOSSID|100497| |LVL|110| |NAME|Ursoc| |MAPID|1094| |ST|This encounter is a single-target encounter with moderate movement requirements. For most groups, the raid should not use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) at the start of the encounter, as (npc:100497) will gain (spell:198388) upon reaching 30% health. Using (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) to reduce the duration of this harder phase of the fight is more likely to allow the raid to succeed.<br/><br/>The central mechanic of the fight is (npc:100497)'s (spell:198006)/(spell:198099)/(spell:199237)/(spell:198109) combo.<br/><br/>(npc:100497) will cast the (spell:198006)/(spell:198099)/(spell:199237)/(spell:198109) combo upon reaching full Energy, every 40 seconds. Because the (spell:198099) debuff lasts 50 seconds, players cannot soak two consecutive (spell:198099) charges.<br/><br/>Before beginning the fight, the raid leader should assign all non-tank players to one of two "soak groups"<br/><br/>These soak groups will alternate soaking the (spell:198099) charge:<br/><br/><b>Group 1 soaks the 1st charge<br/><b>Group 2 soaks the 2nd charge<br/><b>Group 1 soaks the 3rd charge<br/><b>Group 2 soaks the 4th charge<br/><br/>Repeat this pattern until the boss is dead<br/><br/>The raid should also mark a position in the center of the room for the (spell:198006) target to run towards<br/><br/>When (npc:100497) chooses his (spell:198006) target, that player should run to the designated position<br/><br/>Players in the designated soak group should move to stand between (npc:100497) and the (spell:198006) target<br/><br/>Players not in the designated soak group should move to (npc:100497)'s side and stand at max melee range to avoid being struck<br/><br/>Healers should use cooldowns to top the raid up after each (spell:198109) hit<br/><br/>Following this strategy ensures that the (spell:198006) target takes vastly reduced (spell:199237) damage, and reduces the (spell:198109) damage by the maximum amount possible, while avoiding deaths to the (spell:198099) debuff.<br/><br/>After the first (spell:198109) of the fight, (npc:100497) will begin to cast (spell:197969).<br/><br/>(spell:197969) damage can be very dangerous, particularly on the tanks, who are already taking extremely high damage in this encounter. To reduce the likelihood that (spell:197969) will kill the tanks, the whole raid should be close enough to (npc:100497) to split the damage. When not actively soaking a (spell:198099) charge, the raid should be loosely clumped up within 25 yards of the boss.<br/><br/>Tanks must also manage two dangerous debuffs throughout the encounter.<br/><br/><b>(npc:100497) will inflict tanks with (spell:197943) and (spell:204859) debuffs<br/><b>(spell:204859) is a very powerful bleed effect, and in conjunction with (spell:197969) or the boss's melee attacks it can threaten a tank<br/><b>(spell:204859)'s bleed lasts 12 seconds, and (npc:100497) casts it every 20 seconds, so it can never stack<br/><b>(spell:197943) deals moderate damage, but increases all Physical damage its target takes by 15%, which includes (spell:197969) and (spell:198109) damage<br/><b>(spell:197943) lasts for 12 seconds and is cast every 10 seconds, so it will stack<br/><b>Additionally, (spell:197943) increases the damage its target takes from (spell:204859) by 150% per stack<br/><b>Tanks must avoid ever having both (spell:197943) and (spell:204859) debuffs at the same time!<br/><b>This requires frequent taunts to ensure one tank takes 2 stacks of (spell:197943) while the other tank takes the (spell:204859)<br/><b>For example, Tank 1 takes the first 2 (spell:197943)s, with Tank 2 taunting between them to take the first (spell:204859)<br/><b>When Tank 1's 2nd (spell:197943) stack falls off, Tank 1 taunts for the next (spell:204859)<br/><b>When Tank 2's (spell:204859) falls off, Tank 2 taunts and will take the next 2 (spell:197943)s<br/><b>Alternate this pattern for the entire fight<br/><br/>Tanks should use Active Mitigation or cooldowns for the application of these debuffs, especially when it lines up with (spell:198109) or (spell:197969) damage.<br/><br/>When (npc:100497) reaches 30% health, he enters a (spell:198388), dealing 20% increased damage and attacking 25% faster<br/><br/>Due to the extreme danger of the (spell:198388) phase, the raid should plan to use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) and a second potion here. Depending on the timing, it may be advantageous to wait for the first (spell:198109) to be cast, and use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) as soon as the raid is back in position, to maximize DPS uptime on the boss during these powerful buffs.| |DPS|<b>If targeted by (spell:198006), run to the center of the room, at least 30 yards away from the boss<br/><b>When it is your group's turn to soak (spell:198099), move to stand behind (npc:100497), in the line between (npc:100497) and the (spell:198006) target<br/><b>Never soak a (spell:198099) if you still have the (spell:198099) debuff<br/><b>Use personal defensive cooldowns when taking (spell:197969) damage, especially just after a (spell:198109)<br/><b>Be sure to align your strongest DPS cooldowns with (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) during (spell:198388)| |HEAL|<b>Tank damage is extremely heavy, especially when a tank has two stacks of (spell:197943)<br/><b>Assign at least one healer to primarily watch tanks, but all healers should top the tanks up after each (spell:198109) or (spell:197969)<br/><b>Use external cooldowns to protect the tanks during the (spell:198388) phase<br/><b>Raid damage is high from (spell:197969) and (spell:198109)<br/><b>Use efficient AoE immediately after these effects<br/><b>Rotate cooldowns for each (spell:198109), and use minor cooldowns as needed for (spell:197969)<br/><b>Be sure to save the largest cooldowns for the (spell:198388) phase, where they may be necessary for (spell:197969) as well as (spell:198109) damage<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:198006), run to the center of the room, at least 30 yards away from the boss<br/><b>When it is your group's turn to soak (spell:198099), move to stand behind (npc:100497), in the line between (npc:100497) and the (spell:198006) target<br/><b>Never soak a (spell:198099) if you still have the (spell:198099) debuff| |TANK|<b>Avoid having both (spell:197943) and (spell:204859) at the same time<br/><b>Managing the tank debuffs requires frequent taunting, as illustrated in the infographic to the right:<br/><br/><b>Tank 1 starts the fight and gains 1 stack of (spell:197943)<br/><b>Tank 2 taunts, and gains (spell:204859)<br/><b>Tank 1 taunts back, and gains a 2nd stack of (spell:197943)<br/><b>Tank 2's (spell:204859) will fall off<br/><b>Tank 2 taunts and takes the next (spell:197943), now having 1 stack<br/><b>Tank 1's (spell:197943) stacks fall off<br/><b>Tank 1 taunts and takes the next (spell:204859)<br/><b>Tank 2 taunts back, and gains a 2nd stack of (spell:197943)<br/><b>Tank 1's (spell:204859) will fall off<br/><b>Tank 1 taunts and takes the next (spell:197943), now having 1 stack<br/><br/><b>Repeat this pattern as much as necessary to defeat (npc:100497)<br/><b>This can be summarized as "every time your co-tank gains a debuff, taunt; every time you lose a debuff, taunt"<br/><b>Use stronger Active Mitigation or cooldowns when tanking while having 2 stacks of (spell:197943)<br/><b>Use your strongest cooldowns for the (spell:198388) phase| 
|BOSSID|102679| |LVL|110| |NAME|Ysondre| |MAPID|1094| |ST|The Dragons of Nightmare encounter is complicated primarily because the identity of the Emerald Dragons in the fight will be different each week. This guide will describe all four bosses, but players on LFR, Normal, and Heroic difficulty will only fight three of the dragons each week.<br/><br/>(npc:102679) is always present, and stays grounded for the entire fight. At the start of an encounter, one of the other three Emerald Dragons will be grounded beside her. A third dragon will be flying overhead, untargetable.<br/><br/>The Dragons of Nightmare share health. When players bring the Dragons to 70% health, the non-(npc:102679) dragon on the ground will take off, and the dragon flying overhead will land. When the Dragons reach 40% health, the two non-(npc:102679) dragons will switch positions again.<br/><br/>When a dragon is in the air, it is effectively inactive - it cannot be targeted and it uses no abilities. Players must only contend with the two "active" dragons on the ground and master their mechanics.<br/><br/>Players standing within 45 yards of an active dragon will receive a debuff named Mark of <Dragon>.<br/><br/><b>So for example, (npc:102679) applies the (spell:203083) debuff, while (npc:102681) applies the (spell:203121) debuff<br/><b>Additional stacks are granted every 10 seconds, as long as the player is still within 45 yards of the dragon<br/><b>If a player reaches 10 stacks of any one dragon's Mark debuff, they enter a (spell:203110) and are stunned for 30 seconds<br/><br/>To avoid this, the raid must split into two equal groups, and tank the two active dragons on opposite sides of the encounter area.<br/><br/>If players ever receive the wrong dragon's debuff, they should move a few yards further toward the edge of the room. As long as tank swaps happen on 6-8 stacks, one accidental stack should never cause a (spell:203110).<br/><br/>A tank swap will also be necessary each time the airborne dr