|BOSSID|104636| |LVL|110| |NAME|Cenarius| |MAPID|1094| |ST|This encounter is a two-phase encounter with moderate to heavy movement requirements. The majority of the fight is spent in the first phase, where the raid will have to contend with a small group of sturdy adds approximately every 80 seconds. Phase 2 begins when (npc:104636) reaches 35% health, or when the sixth wave of adds has been summoned, and is mostly a single-target burn phase.<br/><br/>The raid should use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) at the beginning of Phase 2.<br/><br/>Throughout the fight, (npc:106482) assists the raid in fighting (npc:104636)'s corruption. At the end of the encounter, (npc:104636) falls unconscious, and (npc:106482) will begin (spell:225790) all traces of the Nightmare from (npc:104636)'s body. Loot is available from a chest that spawns where (npc:104636) began the encounter.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Forces of Nightmare!<br/><br/><b>The most important task of this first phase is dealing with the (spell:212726) mechanic. This is the ability (npc:104636) uses to summon adds, and these adds provide most of the difficulty and complexity of the fight.<br/><b>When (npc:104636) reaches full Energy - shortly into the fight, as he starts on 90/100, and every 80 seconds thereafter - he will cast (spell:212726), creating three (npc:104793)s at predetermined locations around the encounter area.<br/><b>There are four types of (npc:104793)s, each producing a different type of add when it "hatches":<br/><br/><b>The (npc:106895) form in the northeast corner and spawn a set of 10 (npc:106304)s<br/><b>(npc:106304)s are flung from the (npc:106895) and spawn along the edges of the encounter area.<br/><b>Each (npc:106304) will choose a target at random and begin pursuing it<br/><b>If the (npc:106304) reaches its target, it will cast (spell:210619), dealing moderate damage to all players within 8 yards<br/><b>The (npc:106304) will then choose another target and pursue it<br/><b>This behavior repeats until the (npc:106304)s are defeated<br/><b>Ranged DPS should kill the (npc:106304)s, and any player targeted by a (npc:106304) should kite it away from the raid.<br/><b>The (npc:106304)s do not truly Fixate on targets; they can be taunted. It is not recommended for tanks to tank the (npc:106304)s, but it may be useful if hybrid classes use taunts to help pull (npc:106304)s away from the raid.<br/><br/><b>The (npc:106898) forms in the northwest corner and spawns a (npc:105494)<br/><b>(npc:105494)s must be tanked, as their melee attacks are quite powerful.<br/><b>The (npc:105494) will occasionally choose a random target for (spell:211192)<br/><b>The Drake turns to face the target while casting the (spell:211192) cast<br/><b>When the cast completes, the Drake channels (spell:211192) for 4 seconds, dealing moderate Shadow damage to players in a cone<br/><b>The raid should stay close to the (npc:105494) so the cone is easier to escape<br/><b>Spread out in a tight circle around the Drake so not too much DPS is lost to movement<br/><b>In addition, when a (npc:105494) reaches 50% health, it deals pulsing damage to the entire raid with (spell:211178). Each pulse buffs the Drake so its Shadow damage - including (spell:211192) damage - is 20% stronger per stack. Players should quickly kill the (npc:105494) once it reaches 50% health, and healers may wish to use CDs.<br/><br/><b>The (npc:106899) forms in the southwest corner and spawns a (npc:105495)<br/><b>(npc:105495)s must be tanked, and require frequent interrupts.<br/><b>The Sisters cast (spell:211368) every 15 seconds, which will heal an enemy unit<br/><b>The healing is delivered as a small up-front heal and an 8-second HoT effect<br/><b>(spell:211368) should be interrupted each time the Sister attempts to cast it<br/><b>If a (spell:211368) cast is successful, the (spell:211368) HoT can be removed from enemies with offensive dispels like (spell:528)<br/><b>In addition, (npc:105495)s will attack the raid with two abilities.<br/><br/><b>Sisters will frequently target random players with a (spell:211507) hurled at the target's location<br/><b>Players within 4 yards of the targeted location will gain the (spell:211507) DoT, dealing light damage every second for 6 seconds<br/><b>(spell:211507) preferentially targets players at range, so the ranged DPS and healers should spread out to limit splash damage<br/><b>Every 20 seconds, (npc:105495)s will target three non-tank players with (spell:211487)<br/><b>These players are slowed by 30% while affected by (spell:211487)<br/><b>After 12 seconds, (spell:211487) will detonate, dealing heavy damage to the target and all other players within the (spell:211487) radius<br/><b>Any other players struck by this damage will gain a (spell:211487) debuff themselves<br/><b>Players targeted with (spell:211487) must move out of the raid until their debuff detonates, so that it does not propagate through the raid.<br/><br/><b>The (npc:106427) forms in the southeast corner and spawns a (npc:105468)<br/><b>The (npc:105468) deals strong melee damage and must be tanked. Its only ability is (spell:211073), which it uses each time it reaches 100 Energy. (spell:211073) deals heavy damage, split evenly amongst all players within 8 yards. If no players are struck, the entire raid takes heavy (spell:211156) damage.<br/><b>The raid should stack up near the (npc:105468) to share the damage from (spell:211073), and healers should use CDs to recover if necessary.<br/><br/><b>It takes about 15 seconds for the (npc:104793)s to "hatch"<br/><b>There may be up to 6 waves of (spell:212726) during the encounter, and the order of adds spawned in each wave is predetermined<br/><b>In some of these waves, (npc:104636) will summon two copies of the same add type<br/><br/>The (spell:212726) are powerful and have high health. The raid will need one tank to pick up the adds while the other tank stays on (npc:104636).<br/><br/>Killing the (spell:212726) takes priority over dealing d