|BOSSID|103769| |LVL|110| |NAME|Xavius| |MAPID|1094| |ST|This encounter has three phases, initiated when (npc:103769) falls beneath certain health thresholds (Phase 2 begins at 65% health, and Phase 3 begins at 30% health).<br/><br/><b>Each phase has a different set of mechanics that players must master<br/><b>Once consistent mechanic is that, each time (npc:103769) reaches 100 Energy, he will summon adds<br/><b>Some of these adds are high-priority burst targets, particularly during Phase 1 and 2<br/><b>These adds are infrequent and players will spend most of their time DPSing (npc:103769)<br/><br/>Three tanks are recommended for this encounter. It is possible to do with only two tanks, and many groups do, but having three tanks will smooth out certain mechanics and may help the raid progress further into the fight. As always, evaluate your own raid's strengths and weaknesses when determining how many players of each role to bring to an encounter.<br/><br/>Corruption Mechanics<br/><br/><b>When the encounter begins, players will be given an Alternate Power Bar to track their Corruption levels. Corruption is gained from several of (npc:103769)'s abilities, and at certain thresholds, players will begin to 'hallucinate' new mechanics that only they can see or be affected by. It is important to avoid gaining Corruption at too fast a rate, as these additional mechanics deal heavy damage on top of the already hectic fight.<br/><b>At 33 Corruption or higher, players will see (npc:105343)s appear in the shadows at the edges of the encounter area.<br/><br/><b>The (npc:105343)s will cast (spell:208860) about every 10 seconds<br/><b>This creates a large pink circle where the Abomination will smash its limb into the ground<br/><b>Players at the center of the circle (near the edge of the encounter area) will take extremely high damage<br/><b>The damage is reduced the further away you are from the center<br/><b>The range is massive, so you cannot fully outrange the ability<br/><b>Run as far away from the center of the AoE as is feasible<br/><br/><b>At 66 Corruption or higher, players will be affected by (spell:206879).<br/><b>When a player reaches 100 Corruption, they will gain the (spell:208431) buff.<br/><br/><b>For 20 seconds, the player's damage and healing is increased by 150%<br/><b>When this buff wears off, the player gains (spell:207409), and becomes mind-controlled<br/><b>The mind-controlled player transforms into a (npc:110732), and will attack players with (spell:225903)<br/><b>The mind-controlled player's health is increased by 150%<br/><b>Creatures of Madness are immune to all CCs except stuns<br/><br/><b>A player who transforms into a (npc:110732) must be killed, taking valuable DPS and resources away from managing (npc:103769) and his mechanics, as well as increasing the likelihood that other players will become mind-controlled.<br/><b>Note that battle resurrections do not clear a player's Corruption. This means that, if you battle res a player who was mind-controlled, they will pop up with full Corruption and immediately enter (spell:208431). Battle resses should not be used on players who die to this mechanic early in the fight, as the raid will simply have to kill them again soon.<br/><br/>The Dream<br/><br/><b>Fortunately, players are not alone in their fight against (npc:103769). The (npc:105245) will spawn twice during the encounter and send half of the party into the Dream, allowing them extra leeway in managing their Corruption.<br/><b>While in the Dream, players' bodies are unconscious, but the players may still interact in the encounter as a (spell:206005) version of themselves.<br/><b>The (spell:206005) will last for 3 minutes or until:<br/><br/><b>The player takes "fatal" damage<br/><b>The player reaches 100 Corruption, and would become mind-controlled<br/><b>In the latter case, the player will benefit fully from the 20-second (spell:208431) buff<br/><br/><b>(spell:206005) players should assist the raid by performing tasks or soaking mechanics that cause Corruption gain, "shielding" the raid from that Corruption.<br/><br/><b>Dreaming tanks should taunt the (npc:103695) or taunt (npc:103769) during (spell:209443)<br/><b>Dreaming healers should be the primary dispellers of tank debuffs<br/><b>Dreaming players should intercept (npc:103694)s, soak (spell:206369)s, and absorb (spell:208385) pools<br/><b>For more information on these mechanics, see the Phase 1 and Phase 2 sections below<br/><br/><b>The goal within the Dream is to protect the raid as much as possible from Corruption gains, and to prolong your stay in the Dream so that you will reach 100 Corruption and gain the (spell:208431) throughput buff. Use cooldowns liberally to help defeat adds or heal through heavy raid damage.<br/><b>When players enter the Dream, they are set to zero Corruption. However, upon leaving the Dream, players are set back to the Corruption levels they had before the Dream began.<br/><b>While in the Dream, players are vulnerable to the Corruption threshold mechanics listed above, and are very likely to see them since they are soaking Corruption mechanics. Use personal damage reduction cooldowns to survive the additional damage these mechanics will deal.<br/><br/>Phase 1: The Descent Into Madness<br/><br/><b>During Phase 1, (npc:103769) will summon (npc:103694) and (npc:103695) adds, and threatens the raid with (spell:206656). The adds are the most important part of this phase as they can cause players to reach high Corruption values.<br/><b>When (npc:103769) reaches 100 Energy, he will summon one of two types of adds: either (npc:103694)s or a (npc:103695).<br/><b>(spell:205741) spawns a (npc:103694), which will cast (spell:205771) on its target<br/><b>Whenever the (npc:103694) intercepts any player, it will cast (spell:217987) on that player, and then despawn.<br/><b>The player targeted by the (spell:205741) should move away from their location as soon as the (npc:103694) spawns, so the whole raid can easily see where the (npc:103694) will be kited. It may be beneficial to mark a location to kite the Terror towards, so that (spell:206005) players will be able to quickly position themselves to intercept the (spell:217987).<br/><b>On the occasions where (npc:103769) casts (spell:210264) instead of summoning a (npc:103694), a (npc:103695) add will spawn.<br/><b>Remember that (npc:103695)s spawn at 1 minute and 2:20 into the fight, and save short-term DPS throughput cooldowns to help kill these adds quickly. Healers should use cooldowns to recover from the (spell:210264) damage (particularly Dreaming healers, whose cooldowns will be refreshed when they exit the Dream anyway).<br/><b>In addition to these adds, (npc:103769) will attack the raid with (spell:206656).<br/><b>(spell:206656) is extremely dangerous, especially while the (npc:103695) is active.<br/><b>Finally, during Phase 1, (npc:103769) attacks the tanks with (spell:206651), a stacking debuff that deals heavy periodic damage.<br/><b>Tanks must run away from the raid before healers can dispel (spell:206651).<br/><b>If you are two-tanking, then the tank who is not in the Dream will be tanking (npc:103769) for a long period of time while the Dream tank handles the (npc:103695). The non-Dreaming tank should save their heaviest cooldowns and active mitigation abilities for this time.<br/><b>If you are three-tanking, then two tanks can continue to swap as normally scheduled for (spell:206651) while the Dream tank handles the (npc:103695).<br/><b>Dreaming healers should be in charge of dispelling the (spell:206651) debuff from tanks.<br/><b>Phase 1 lasts until (npc:103769) reaches 65% health. Avoid pushing (npc:103769) to Phase 2 with a (npc:103695) still alive.<br/><br/>Phase 2: From the Shadows<br/><br/><b>During Phase 2, (npc:103769) will summon (npc:105611) adds, and threatens the raid with (spell:206369) and (spell:210451). <br/><b>Each time (npc:103769) reaches 100 Energy, he will cast (spell:205588), summoning a set of (npc:105611)s.<br/><b>When an (npc:105611) gets close to (npc:103769), it will begin to channel (spell:209288).<br/><b>The raid should kill (npc:105611)s quickly, and use slows/stuns/CC abilities to keep them away from (npc:103769). Melee DPS and non-tanking tanks should attack the nearest Horrors, while ranged DPS should attack Horrors further from the boss.<br/><b>When an (npc:105611) dies, it dissolves into a (spell:208385) pool.<br/><b>Approximately every 30 seconds, (npc:103769) will target a player with (spell:206369).<br/><b>Players with (spell:206005) should help split the (spell:206369) damage, while players who are not in the Dream should avoid it.<br/><b>In Phase 2, (npc:103769) attacks the tanks with (spell:209158), a stacking debuff that deals heavy periodic damage.<br/><b>Due to the 30-second (spell:205612) debuff, tanks should swap every 3-4 stacks. The periodic damage is very high at these stack levels, so be sure to use stronger cooldowns or active mitigation to survive. Run slightly away from the other tanks before calling for a dispel, so that only players with the (spell:209443) will soak the (spell:208385).<br/><b>Dreaming healers should be in charge of dispelling the (spell:209158) debuff from tanks.<br/><b>Additionally, (npc:103769) will buff himself with (spell:209443), causing his melee attacks to also grant his target 5 Corruption.<br/><b>Phase 2 lasts until (npc:103769) reaches 30% health. Make sure not to push (npc:103769) to Phase 3 until all (spell:208385) pools have been absorbed - (spell:209288) during Phase 3 will surely cause wipes.<br/><br/>Phase 3: World of Darkness<br/><br/><b>The final phase of the encounter is a hectic burn phase. The raid must defeat (npc:103769) before the inevitable Corruption gains lead to too many players transforming into Creatures of Madness and causing wipes.<br/><b>Use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) during this phase. Using strong cooldowns at the start of the phase will help remove a large chunk of (npc:103769)'s health before the fight becomes too hectic.<br/><b>When (npc:103769) reaches 100 Energy during this phase, he will cast (spell:226194).<br/><b>(npc:104592)s are a constant source of unavoidable Corruption gains, but the raid must balance killing the Tentacles with killing (npc:103769).<br/><b>(npc:103769) will continue to use abilities from both Phase 1 and Phase 2 throughout this final phase.<br/><b>Because this phase is a race against the Corruption bar, the raid must do its best to spread out these Corruption gains.<br/><b>It is very likely that at least some players will reach 100 Corruption during this phase. Ideally, these players can use the (spell:208431) buff to deal extremely high damage to (npc:103769) and end the encounter before the buff expires. If any players become mind-controlled, the raid will have to decide whether they can ignore/stun them and keep attacking (npc:103769), or if they need to quickly kill off the player.<br/><br/>Note that three tanks are recommended for this encounter.<br/><br/><b>Tanks can use cooldowns more aggressively since they will be tanking (npc:103769) less frequently, allowing healers to dispel less frequently<br/><b>This allows healers to stay in the Dream longer during Phases 1 and 2<br/><b>Managing tank swaps around the (npc:103695) and (spell:209443) mechanics becomes more forgiving<br/><b>During Phase 3, three tanks can spread out the (spell:209443)'s Corruption gains to lower the chance that any tank will succumb to (spell:207409)<br/><br/>"Dream Team" Responsibilities<br/><br/><b>Each player in the raid will enter the Dream state once in the fight. It is important that all members of the raid know what to do when they become a (spell:206005).<br/><br/>During Phase 1:<br/><br/><b>Tank: Tank the (npc:103695) off to one side of the raid<br/><b>DPS: Intercept the (npc:103694) adds to protect others from (spell:217987)<br/><b>Healer: Dispel the (spell:206651) debuff after each tank swap<br/><br/>During Phase 2:<br/><br/><b>Tank: Taunt (npc:103769) when he is buffed by (spell:209443)<br/><b>DPS: Stand in the (spell:208385) puddles that form after killing (npc:105611)s, and help split (spell:206369) damage<br/><b>Healer: Dispel the (spell:209158) debuff after each tank swap<br/><br/><b>Use cooldowns freely, as they will be restored when you leave the (spell:206005) state<br/><b>Healing cooldowns are useful to counteract (spell:210264) in Phase 1, or (spell:206369) in Phase 2<br/><b>DPS cooldowns are useful to kill adds - the (npc:103695)s in Phase 1, or (npc:105611)s in Phase 2<br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 33 Corruption, run away from the (spell:208860) effects<br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 66 Corruption, move away from the (spell:206879) zones| |DPS|Phase 1:<br/><br/><b>All DPS should switch to the (npc:103695) when it spawns<br/><b>Move away from (spell:205741) to avoid (spell:217987) damage<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206656), quickly move out to the side of the raid group<br/><b>Stay far away from the designated location to dispel the tank's (spell:206651) debuff<br/><br/>Phase 2:<br/><br/><b>All DPS must switch immediately to the (npc:105611)s near them<br/><b>Melee DPS should attack the (npc:105611)s near the boss, while ranged should attack the ones behind the raid<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206369), move to the designated location so (spell:206005) players can help soak its damage<br/><br/>Phase 3:<br/><br/><b>Only attack (npc:104592)s that spawn within comfortable cleave/AoE range, or with multi-DoT abilities<br/><b>Mostly maximize your single-target DPS on (npc:103769) to defeat the fight before the entire raid succumbs to (spell:208431)<br/><b>Use your most powerful cooldowns here to align with (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353)<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206656), quickly move out to the side of the raid group<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206369), stay stacked in the raid so the maximum number of players can help soak its damage<br/><br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 33 Corruption, run away from the (spell:208860) effects<br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 66 Corruption, move away from the (spell:206879) zones| |HEAL|<b>Use cooldowns on tanks at high stacks of (spell:206651) or (spell:209158)<br/><b>Use raid cooldowns for (spell:210264) and (spell:206369) damage, and again during Phase 3 as often as possible<br/><b>During Phases 1 and 2, only dispel (spell:206651)/(spell:209158) if you are in the (spell:206005)<br/><b>If no healers are in the (spell:206005), or during Phase 3, the healer with the lowest Corruption should dispel tanks<br/><b>Players targeted by (spell:206656), (spell:206369), or (spell:210451), and players over 33 Corruption, will require additional healing<br/><b>Move away from (spell:205741) to avoid (spell:217987) damage<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206656), quickly move out to the side of the raid group<br/><b>If targeted by (spell:206369), move to the designated location<br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 33 Corruption, run away from the (spell:208860) effects<br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 66 Corruption, move away from the (spell:206879) zones| |TANK|Phase 1:<br/><br/><b>Take as many stacks of (spell:206651) as you can survive, using heavier cooldowns at higher stacks<br/><b>Run away to a designated location for (spell:206651) to be dispelled<br/><b>Only the Dream tank should taunt and tank the (npc:103695)<br/><b>Face the Horror away from the raid so  Tormenting Swipe does not hit any other players<br/><br/>Phase 2:<br/><br/><b>Take as many stacks of (spell:209158) as you can survive, using heavier cooldowns at higher stacks<br/><b>The Dream tank should taunt (npc:103769) for the duration of the (spell:209443) buff<br/><b>Move (npc:103769) away from approaching (npc:105611)s if possible<br/><br/>Phase 3:<br/><br/><b>Time tank swaps so that a different tank is tanking for each of (npc:103769)'s (spell:209443) buffs<br/><b>Drag (npc:103769) near clumps of (npc:104592)s only if it is convenient to do so<br/><b>Use cooldowns frequently to help the healers, as raid damage during this phase is very high<br/><br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 33 Corruption, run away from the (spell:208860) effects<br/><b>At all times, if you have more than 66 Corruption, move away from the (spell:206879) zones| 
|BOSSID|114263| |LVL|110| |NAME|Odyn| |MAPID|1114| |ST|(npc:114263) is a three phase encounter which requires the raid to deal damage in a controlled way whilst dealing with mechanics from multiple sources simultaneously. Excellent communication and coordination skills are needed to prove your worth to (npc:114263) once again! <br/><br/>Phase 1 consists of (npc:114361) and (npc:114360). Your objective in this phase is to get both bosses to cast (spell:228171) at the same time so you can transition into phase 2.<br/><br/><b>This spell is cast once either (npc:114361) or (npc:114360) reach 25% health.<br/><b>During this phase you need to dodge the (spell:228003) from (npc:114361) and make sure you are not within 5 yards of others when (spell:228012) is cast.<br/><b>(spell:228030) must be spot healed.<br/><b>(spell:228162) should hit as many players as possible to spread the damage.<br/><b>(npc:114361) and (npc:114360) must be 35 yards or more apart to prevent (spell:228018) from being an issue.<br/><b>You also have to deal with (npc:114996)'s to prevent (npc:114263)'s (spell:227629) from becoming empowered.<br/><br/>Phase 2 (npc:114263) will join the encounter and force you to deal with his (spell:228162).<br/><br/><b>(spell:231016) causes large, consistent and bursty damage on your raid.<br/><b>You also have to deal with (npc:114996)'s to prevent (npc:114263)'s (spell:227629) from becoming empowered.<br/><br/>Phase 3 starts once (npc:114263) hits 55% health. (npc:114263) will gain an entirely new set of abilities.<br/><br/><b>You must defeat him before his (spell:229255) becomes too powerful for your healers to cope with.<br/><b>(spell:227807) tornadoes need to be placed away from fellow raid members whilst everyone needs to keep clear of areas coated in (spell:227475).<br/><b>Tanks effected by (spell:228915) must travel as far from the boss as possible and taunt on one stack of the debuff.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Might of the Valarjar<br/><br/><b>Phase 1 consists of fighting two mini-bosses, (npc:114361) and (npc:114360), whilst (npc:114263) watches from his throne.<br/><b>While (npc:114361) and (npc:114360) are within 35 yards of each other their damage taken is reduced by 99% as a result of (spell:228018). In order to deal meaningful damage to the minibosses, you must have them spread at least 35 yards throughout the phase.<br/><br/>(npc:114361)<br/><br/><b>Every 35 seconds (npc:114361) will cast (spell:228012).<br/><b>This 4 second cast will deal a large amount of damage to anyone within 15 yards, as well as a moderate amount of damage to each individual member of the raid and splash additional damage to anyone within 5 yards of them.<br/><b>Tanks and any melee DPS must move away from (npc:114361) during the cast, whilst the raid should be spread apart from one another by 5 yards to avoid the splash damage aspect of the ability.<br/><b>(npc:114361) will throw a (spell:228003) towards random ranged player, dealing damage upon impact and consistent damage to anyone who stands within it<br/><br/>(npc:114360)<br/><br/><b>(spell:228030) will be applied to a random player in your raid. The player with (spell:228030) should move 8 yards away from anyone else in order to avoid unnecessary extra damage to the raid.<br/><b>Every 35 seconds (npc:114360) will cast (spell:228162)<br/><b>She will face and track a player for 3 seconds. She will then send out a large beam of light towards them, dealing a large amount of damage and knocking them back.<br/><b>The damage and knockback aspect of this ability is shared between all players hit.<br/><b>The player who is fixated by the (spell:228162) should point her targeting arrow towards the middle of the room and then remain still, whilst any nearby players, including the tank and melee DPS on (npc:114360), stand within the beam to help spread the damage.<br/><b>Because (npc:114360) and (npc:114361) need to be brought to 25% health within a 10 second window, it is very important that you spread your DPS across them.<br/><b>We recommend having the majority of your melee DPS focused on (npc:114360), whilst the ranged dps mainly focus on (npc:114361). This is due to (npc:114361)'s (spell:228012) cast being unfriendly to your melee DPS, whilst (npc:114360)'s (spell:228162) cast can be easily countered by having your melee DPS soak it.<br/><b>You will need to monitor the health of both mini-bosses, and make adjustments to your assignments depending on your DPS composition, to ensure that they both reach 25% health within those 10 seconds.<br/><br/>(npc:114263)<br/><br/><b>Although (npc:114263) is out of the encounter area and is not damageable in this phase, he will cast a (spell:227503).<br/><b>All 5 runes of power will activate on the floor and he will begin to generate energy.<br/><b>30 seconds later, after he reaches 100 energy he will cast (spell:227629) which deals large raid wide damage.<br/><b>The damage of the (spell:227629) is increased by 200% for each rune active on the ground.<br/><b>The raid must disable the runes by killing the (npc:114996) that spawn around the sides of the room at the same time (spell:227503) is cast.<br/><b>(npc:114996)'s will fixate a player and mark them with a symbol which matches a rune on the floor.<br/><b>Players who are fixated must drag the (npc:114996) to the rune that matches the one they have been branded with in order to remove the (spell:227598) which reduces all damage taken by the (npc:114996) by 99%.<br/><b>Once inside the (npc:114996)s must die, which deactivates the rune, before the (spell:227629) cast goes off. This will reduce the damage of the (spell:227629) causing it to be survivable by the raid.<br/><b>You should have all DPS switch to the Runebearers to make sure that they die in time.<br/><br/>Once (npc:114361) and (npc:114360) reach 25% health within 10 seconds of one another they will leave the encounter area. (npc:114263) will then enter the encounter area and phase 2 will begin.<br/><br/>Phase 2: The 