|BOSSID|114344| |LVL|110| |NAME|Guarm| |MAPID|1114| |ST|(npc:114344) is a single phase encounter which tests your raids ability to deal high single target damage whilst dealing with simple yet devastating mechanics. When making composition choices for this encounter, do consider bringing the highest single target damage possible as the enrage timer is just 5 minutes long. <br/><br/>Most important to note is that each of (npc:114344)'s 3 heads will cast (spell:228187).<br/><br/><b>One will cast (spell:227539) (red), another (spell:227566) (pale blue) and the last (spell:227570) (purple).<br/><b>All three breaths do a large amount of damage split between all players hit, whilst applying an element specific debuff which will instantly kill a player if they take a breath of a different element.<br/><b>For each player not hit by any of the breaths, (npc:114344) will gain a stack of (spell:228174) which permanently increases his damage by 5%.<br/><br/>Tanks should face (npc:114344) to the raid at all times to lower the movement required by raid members to get into the various breath cones<br/><br/>(spell:227514) will deal high damage to all players within a 25 yard cone in front of (npc:114344). This ability causes positioning conflicts, as you need to have the front of (npc:114344) readily accessible for his (spell:228187) ability. To counter this there are 2 working strategies:<br/><br/><b>Strategy 1 - Face (npc:114344) away from the raid for the majority of the fight and turn to face the group when the (spell:228187) ability is coming in.<br/><b>Strategy 2 - Have your ranged DPS at least 25 yards in front of (npc:114344), with the melee stacked just behind (npc:114344) himself.<br/><br/>Strategy 1 would work perfectly assuming you have timers that are 100% accurate, whereas Strategy #2 allows you to keep (npc:114344) perfectly still and have the melee DPS move in front of him during the (spell:228187). We recommend having the ranged DPS at least 25 yards in front of (npc:114344), with the melee DPS stacked up behind him, however the choice is yours. <br/><br/>When (spell:227883) is cast (npc:114344) will knock back all players within 25 yards. He will then select the largest clump of players and jump on them, dealing a moderate amount of physical damage and knocking them into the air.<br/><br/>Tanks need to remain stacked on one another, as each melee attack will also hit the closest player within 8 yards through (spell:227512). If nobody else is present within 8 yards, the tank will be hit twice. This will also mean that both tanks will be taking damage throughout the fight, healers need to make sure that both remain healthy.<br/><br/>When (spell:227816) begins, (npc:114344) will jump into one of the four corners of the encounter area and run down one side. Once he reaches the end he will turn around and run down the opposite side. This happens every 60 seconds or so.<br/><br/>(npc:114344) has 3 different lick debuffs that are randomly applied to ranged players. The debuff will also be applied to any players within 5 yards of the initial player also. It's fundamental that you're spread 5 yards to avoid them spreading.<br/><br/><b>(spell:228228) deals significant pulsing area of effect damage to players within 5 yards.<br/><b>(spell:228246) will instantly stun a random ranged player for 5 seconds. This effect can be dispelled.<br/><b>(spell:228250) players need to be spot healed by healers to remove the healing absorption debuff.<br/><br/>All three of these debuffs can be devastating, so it is of the utmost importance that ranged players remain spread out. If a raid composition consists of a high amount of melee DPS, they may also need to spread out as well. <br/><br/>(spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) timing on this boss can be incredibly important since the fight has such a short enrage timer.| |DPS|<b>Split your raid into three groups and have each group soak one of the elemental breaths when (spell:228187) is cast. Each player will need to soak that same elemental breath type for the rest of the encounter.<br/><b>Ranged players need to remain spread 5 yards at all times to minimize the effects of Guardian Licks abilities.<br/><b>The raid should position so that the ranged players are at least 25 yards in front of (npc:114344)'s face, with the melee DPS stacked up behind him. This will reduce the effect of his (spell:227514).<br/><b>Everyone needs to move out of the way of the (spell:227816) and the tanks need to be ready to quickly position (npc:114344) afterwards, ready for the next (spell:228187) or (spell:227514).<br/><b>Melee DPS should remain stacked up during (spell:227883) to ensure that the boss will jump onto them, rather than the ranged players.<br/><b>Have BIG DPS - Kill (npc:114344) within 5 minutes!| |HEAL|<b>Healers need to make sure they dispel the (spell:228246) stun and heal up the (spell:228250) healing absorption shield.<br/><b>The raid should position so that the ranged players are at least 25 yards in front of (npc:114344)'s face, with the melee DPS stacked up behind him. This will reduce the effect of his (spell:227514).<br/><b>Everyone needs to move out of the way of the (spell:227816) and the tanks need to be ready to quickly position (npc:114344) afterwards, ready for the next (spell:228187) or (spell:227514).| |TANK|<b>Split your raid into three groups and have each group soak one of the elemental breaths when (spell:228187) is cast. Each player will need to soak that same elemental breath type for the rest of the encounter.<br/><b>Tanks need to remain stacked on top of one another to spread the damage of (spell:227512).<br/><b>Everyone needs to move out of the way of the (spell:227816) and the tanks need to be ready to quickly position (npc:114344) afterwards, ready for the next (spell:228187) or (spell:227514).| 
|BOSSID|114537| |LVL|110| |NAME|Helya| |MAPID|1114| |ST|(npc:114537) is a three phase encounter which demands high single target and multi-target damage from players, coupled with quick reactions in order to counter devastating mechanics.<br/><br/><b>Phase 1 consists of fighting (npc:114537) directly, whilst dealing with (npc:116195)s quickly before they annihilate the raid.<br/><b>At 65% health phase 2 will begin and (npc:114537) will retreat away from the encounter area, players will have to deal with waves of various adds whilst destroying (npc:114537)'s (npc:114901)s that are scattered throughout the encounter area.<br/><b>Once all (npc:114901)s are destroyed, (npc:114537) will return and phase 3 will begin. Phase 3 mixes various abilities from phase 1 and 2 with slight mechanical changes to these abilities.<br/><br/>Phase 1: Low Tide<br/><br/><b>During phase 1, your raid will be fighting (npc:114537) directly until she reaches 65% health. It is important that a member of your raid is always within melee range of (npc:114537), otherwise she will cast (spell:228872). She will deal a burst of damage to the raid and gain a 3% damage increase. This effect stacks. Players effected by (spell:228054) will take moderate ticking damage until dispelled.<br/><b>(npc:115166) will frequently spawn on the location of a few members of the raid.<br/><br/><b>Each orb will then fixate their player and chase after them for 8 seconds whilst pulsing out moderate aoe damage to anyone nearby.<br/><b>If a player takes damage from the orb, they will take 100% extra damage from the next hit of the orb. This effect stacks.<br/><b>Players should remain spread out when (spell:227903) is due to come in to help minimize any accidental damage they might take.<br/><b>The player fixated by the orb should kite it away from the group, towards the edges of the room.<br/><b>The (spell:227903) will always pick the off-tank and then random ranged players. The off-tank needs plan their movement so that they will be back within range of (npc:114537) by the time they need to taunt her (spell:230229).<br/><br/><b>Every 25 seconds (npc:114537) will cast (spell:230229), a large conal breath directed towards the tank which deals moderate magic damage to all players hit whilst applying (spell:227982), a 30 second debuff that reduces armor by 100%. The breath will also cause 5 (npc:116195) adds to spawn.<br/><b>When the (spell:230229) comes in, you want to face it to one side of the platform whilst making sure not to face it too far away from the encounter area, as otherwise the (npc:116195)s will spawn on top of the elevated platforms. Once the breath comes in, have the off-tank taunt to help mitigate the effects of (spell:227982). <br/><b>All DPS should then focus down the adds, dealing as much damage to all of them at once.<br/><b>A tentacle will periodically emerge at either the front or back of the platform. <br/><br/><b>Shortly after spawning the tentacle will slam into the ground, inflicting a large amount of damage split between all players within its targeting area.<br/><b>If the tentacle hits the ground and no player is within the targeting area, it cast (spell:231298) which will deal a huge amount of damage to the entire raid, which in most cases is lethal.<br/><b>It is important that you have as many people soak the (spell:228767) as is convenient, to help split the damage between all players hit.<br/><b>You are able to have a player use an immunity ((spell:186265)/(spell:45438)) and then soak the (spell:228767) by themselves. This helps reduce the damage taken by the raid substantially, whilst allowing players to spread out for abilities such as (spell:228054) and (spell:227903).<br/><b>If you have access to these immunities, we recommend using them on the (spell:228767)s that occur at the back of the platform, as less members of the raid are going to be able to soak that without large downtimes in comparison to the tentacle that spawns at the front.<br/><br/>Once (npc:114537) reaches 65% health, she will retreat away from the encounter area and will no longer be damageable directly. Try and ensure that the encounter area is clear of (npc:116195)s before the transition to allow you to deal with phase 2 straight from the outset.<br/><br/>Phase 2: From the Mists<br/><br/><b>(npc:114537) will assault the raid from afar, whilst the denizens of Helmeim fight the raid directly. It is the job of the raid to kill off (npc:114537)'s (npc:114901)s which are scattered around the encounter area, whilst fighting off the denizens of Helmeim and surviving (npc:114537)'s long range spells. 9 (npc:114901)s will spawn in the encounter area, Three at the back, 2 on each elevated platform and one on the ground floor by the side of each elevated platform.<br/><b>(npc:114537) will be dealing small burst of damage to random members of the raid throughout the phase with her (spell:228514) spell. This damage ramps up, as each (spell:228514) cast buffs (npc:114537) with (spell:228803), increasing (spell:228514) damage by 5% per stack. This ability acts as a pseudo-enrage for the phase, as you need to transition into phase 3 before this (spell:228514) damage becomes overwhelming. (npc:114537) will cast (spell:228032) on a timer. This causes a large wave will travel across the lower parts of the encounter area, dealing a small amount of damage and pushing players back every half-second.<br/><b>On the first (spell:228032) cast right at the beginning of phase 2, and at the end of each barrage of (spell:228032) casts from that point onwards, two large adds will spawn, one on each side of the encounter area. One (npc:114812) and One (npc:114709).<br/><b>Once the Mariner is dead, swap to the (npc:114709). Make sure you avoid the (spell:228390). The (npc:114709) remains stationary during this cast, so the tank and melee should move 15 yards away from the (npc:114709) to avoid the ability.<br/><b>(spell:193367) will also be applied on players from the (npc:114709).<br/><b>The (npc:114709) should be tanked separately away from the (npc:114812), so that the melee DPS can attack the Mariner without having to deal with the movement based mechanics of the (npc:114709).<br/><b>Waves of (npc:114568)s will spawn around the edges of the room.<br/><b>The raid should stack up to help group up the (npc:114568)s and then cleave them down.<br/><b>After all 9 (npc:114901)s have been killed, you will transition into phase 3. When you transition, all adds that are active will remain active and will continue to harass your raid. You want to try and minimize the amount of adds active before heading into phase 3.<br/><br/>Phase 3: Helheim's Last Stand<br/><br/><b>Phase three consists of a mixture of abilities that are similar to the ones seen in both phase 1 & 2. Many of these abilities place leave slime on the ground which persists until cleared by the (spell:228032) waves, therefore this phase forces players to use the space they are given wisely. (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) should be used in this phase with DPS cooldowns to finish the encounter as soon as possible. (npc:114537) will still cast (spell:228872) if no players are within melee range. She will also still cast (spell:228054). The (npc:114812) will still spawn.<br/><b>When (spell:228565) is cast, face it away from the raid.<br/><b>Instead of (npc:115166), (npc:114537) will now spawn (npc:114566).<br/><b>The (npc:114568)s will spawn in waves around the edges of the room, fixate a target and melee hit them whilst slowly gaining damage through (spell:14983).<br/><b>When (spell:228032) is cast, a large wave will travel through the lower parts of the encounter area, dealing damage and pushing back players every half-second.| |DPS|Phase 1<br/><br/><b>Be spread for when the (spell:227903) is cast and have the fixated players kite the orbs away from the raid.<br/><b>Have the majority of the raid, or a single player with an immunity, soak the slam from the (spell:228767) to avoid (spell:231298) from wiping the raid.<br/><b>Have all DPS focus down the (npc:116195)s to reduce the severity of (spell:227990).<br/><b>Make sure no (npc:116195)s are active before transitioning at 65% health.<br/><br/>Phase 2<br/><br/><b>Move as a single unit to an elevated platform during the (spell:228032) waves.<br/><b>Kill off the (npc:114812) before the (spell:228619) is cast, whilst having the tank use active mitigation during his (spell:228611). Ranged players should also move out of the (spell:228631) cast.<br/><b>Move away from the (npc:114709) during his (spell:228390) and have the tank use large damage reductions for the (spell:228519).<br/><b>Move 5 yards away from your allies when (spell:193367) is going to time out, to prevent it from spreading to them.<br/><b>Group up, crowd control and kill the (npc:114568)s. Make sure they die on the lower sections of the room, so that the (spell:228121) they leave is washed away by the (spell:228032) waves.<br/><b>Kill off all 9 (npc:114901)s spread around the edges of the encounter area to progress into phase 3.<br/><br/>Phase 3<br/><br/><b>Group up, crowd control and kill the (npc:114568)s, make sure they die on the lower sections of the room so that the (spell:228121) they leave is washed away by a (spell:228032) wave. It is also important they die close together so you can maximize the amount of room the raid has.<br/><b>Kill off the (npc:114812) before the (spell:228619) is cast, whilst having the tank use active mitigation during his (spell:228611). Ranged player should also move out of the (spell:228631) cast.<br/><b>Be spread for when the (spell:228058) is cast and have the fixated players kite the orbs around the edges of the room. Keep the patches of (spell:228121) they leave in their wake close together to maximise the room the raid has.<br/><b>Use (spell:2825)/(spell:32182)/(spell:80353) during this phase when dps cooldowns align.| |HEAL|Phase 1<br/><br/><b>Be spread for when the (spell:227903) is cast and have the fixated players kite the orbs away from the raid.<br/><b>Quickly dispel the (spell:228054) debuff and move out of the (spell:228051) it leaves on the ground.<br/><b>Have the majority of the raid, or a single player with an immunity, soak the slam from the (spell:228767) to avoid (spell:231298) from wiping the raid.<br/><br/>Phase 2<br/><br/><b>Move as a single unit to an elevated platform during the (spell:228032) waves.<br/><b>Move away from the (npc:114709) during his (spell:228390) and have the tank use large damage reductions for the (spell:228519).<br/><b>Move 5 yards away from your allies when (spell:193367) is going to time out, to prevent it from spreading to them.<br/><b>Group up, crowd control and kill the (npc:114568)s. Make sure they die on the lower sections of the room, so that the (spell:228121) they leave is washed away by the (spell:228032) waves.<br/><br/>Phase 3<br/><br/><b>Group up, crowd control and kill the (npc:114568)s, make sure they die on the lower sections of the room so that the (spell:228121) they leave is washed away by a (spell:228032) wave. It is also important they die close together so you can maximize the amount of room the raid has.<br/><b>Be spread for when the (spell:228058) is cast and have the fixated players kite the orbs around the edges of the room. Keep the patches of (spell:228121) they leave in their wake close together to maximise the room the raid has.<br/><b>Use a healing cooldown when the (spell:228032) wave washes across the encounter area. Alternatively, avoid the damage it deals by moving to an elevated platform.| |TANK|Phase 1<br/><br/><b>Make sure a tank is always within melee range to counteract (spell:228872).<br/><b>Be spread for when the (spell:227903) is cast and have the fixated players kite the orbs away from the raid.<br/><b>Face (npc:114537) towards one side of the room for the (spell:230229), make sure that no (npc:116195)s spawn on the elevated sections of the platform.<br/>